Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.82,0:01:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we share our spiritual experience and what has come about in the transformation of our own life\Nwith others so what we do is we carry the message and we carry the message primarily
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.38,0:01:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,intuitively and in the non-verbal although we describe the events within the verbal\Nthe person gets from your aura what that is and it's the energy that you bring to the person
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.73,0:01:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and not your conversation so the conversation is because you got to say something in this world\Nand you hope the message might grab them but you only share it because spirituality grows by
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.48,0:01:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,attraction and not promotion which is another principle of the 12-step recovery groups you never\Nsee 12-step groups proselytizing nobody tries to get you to give up smoking drinking sex or whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.81,0:01:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they tell you i\Nused to be an abusive person and i had a terrible temper and i hit my wife a couple times and i
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.65,0:02:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,landed in court and and i really was scared and i couldn't stop it i couldn't stop it\Nand then i went to such and such a group and now everything is healed and i've learned how to handle
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.04,0:02:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it and i learned a lot about myself in the process and i'm a different person and the\Nperson i've become now doesn't hit people so it's by transformation so spiritual steps then
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.40,0:02:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,are designed to bring\Nabout a transformation so we thought i thought i'd give a little time to the 12 steps because
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.71,0:02:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they have such a profound effect on our society beyond people's awareness\Npeople who are familiar with this very these various groups pick up a concept just like that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.18,0:02:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and i hear people in extremely high places in the world just with a simple remark i know\Nhow he cuts over and why he feels spiritually committed to what he's committed to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.58,0:02:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Njust one word will tell you what their background is spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.00,0:03:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so that pervades a great part of our current society see our society was at 190\Nhuman society was at 190 it's now at 207 well it didn't pull itself up by its bootstraps you can
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.81,0:03:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,see that by the pure nature of the ego in and of itself the ego isn't going to give up any turf\Nwhatsoever so the spiritually committed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.55,0:03:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,people in our society are influencing others by virtue of that which they have become\Nnot by proselytizing not by preaching but by by that which they have become in the presence of a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.37,0:03:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,more spiritually evolved person it is quite difficult to be vulgar and violent and selfish\Nyou start to feel uncomfortable about it you felt okay with it on the street where it's the style
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.22,0:04:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but as you start to present the same story\Nto more spiritually evolved people you see them change at the girls ranch where i've been for 12
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.71,0:04:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,years i'm going to have to resign from there do like a time but we see hopeless i found another\Ndoctor to come in so i've treated you know a thousand thousand teenagers highly resistant
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.06,0:04:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,savage backgrounds brutality brutality so extreme you say this is not possible this is not possible\Nand i won't even describe it here the experience is not possible and i won't even describe it here
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.77,0:04:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiences are so grotesque so extreme you say that's not even possible i don't want to even\Nhear their history social workers starts to tell me this is their history i said i don't want to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.93,0:04:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,hear it i just accept it's catastrophic and how can anybody recover from that how can anybody\Npossibly recover from that it went on for years for instance and how can they well i'll tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.89,0:05:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,they can't ptsd dude that said savagery you can't recover\Nthere's no psychological technique there's no medicine there's no physical healing you cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.17,0:05:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so how can you recover from it only by the miraculous the power of love\Nso each month the girl comes in and you watch the transformation from ferociously angry ferociously
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.44,0:06:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,depressed assaultive suicidal they cut on themselves all the time they try to overdose\Nkill themselves and you watch gradually the flower blooming so you see that which is possible
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.86,0:06:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,only by love only love could bring it out of that savagery into become a beautiful young person\Nso the damage then is spiritual and the recovery then is spiritual the people below 200 are
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.87,0:06:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you can look at them as severely damaged spiritually whether it's by their own election\Nwhether it's by karmic fate or by what up for whatever reason we now see that they are
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.83,0:07:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually damaged people other than a powerful field this powerful field here is so powerful\Nthat it pulls the miraculous forth in those who have karmic permission to do so
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.74,0:07:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't always happen in this lifetime and you don't know with the reason for it you would have to\Nsee the karmic path away so you don't know what the reason for it you would have to see the karmic path
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.60,0:07:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the lifetimes, all the decisions, the context of it all,\Nthe karmic pattern of the country, the ethnic group, the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.66,0:07:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You would have to know a great deal.\NThat's why all the steps that are profoundly powerful then
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.32,0:07:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,all require surrender of one's willingness and they all require humility.\NI don't know why this one recovered and that one didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.64,0:07:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But the miraculous is commonplace.\NThey should never have been able to get up and walk again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.69,0:07:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we surrender, we start from the ego position.\NGuilt, we share our shortcomings with other people, we look at ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.69,0:08:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and we constantly refer what's in the field to the field itself.\NWe ask God for help. We constantly turn our life over to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.69,0:08:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We pray to God for understanding. We pray to God for direction.\NSo we're constantly moving our tentacles out into the field
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.31,0:08:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and we say, in and of ourselves, we are unable to help ourselves.\NIt's only by the spiritual truth of those who have evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.04,0:08:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, everyone here, by merely being here to this day,\Nis already serving all of mankind. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.04,0:08:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the advance, just your own willingness.\NYour willingness to advance your own consciousness already uplifts mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.03,0:08:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, what can I do for the world?\NYou're doing it. You're doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.03,0:08:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of spiritual commitment uplifts by its own nature\Nbecause it uplifts the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.03,0:09:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In previous lectures, we tried to align that for the skeptical\Nwith Henry Stapp's email or what do you call that website thing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.42,0:09:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of Berkeley with the quantum mechanics.\NHow he correlates quantum mechanics with how everything works.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.51,0:09:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So every spiritual decision uplifts the field of mankind\Nand that the field then lifts each one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.90,0:09:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So each one of us then is contributing to the rise of the water, you might say.\NAnd as the water rises, it lifts all the ships,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.90,0:09:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what their size, that are afloat.\NSo consciousness is like the sea. We uplift everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.28,0:09:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So every girl at the girl's ranch recovers, helps every other recover.\NAnd we see great inspirational stories of people
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.22,0:09:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,who have been savaged early in their life.\NInstead of falling into and buying victimhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.22,0:09:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,they bought the spiritual way out.\NAnd we see people of great prominence,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:10:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the most famous people in the world had savage backgrounds\Nand they stand for the recovery through spiritual principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.37,0:10:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only through spirituality that recovery from that\Nand these things can come about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we've got a short time before lunch.\NI thought, let's try something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.79,0:10:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of just reading the questions out loud,\Nanybody who wants to come up and talk to us, let's talk to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.83,0:10:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to be on, you know, everybody's going to hear it.\NSo we're going to share what goes on with everyone and come on up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.01,0:10:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll just come on up and gather around\Nand we'll just begin to really discuss things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.01,0:10:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got 15 minutes and then we'll take a break for lunch.\NWe'll try it. We'll try it for 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.21,0:10:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So everybody who's got a question, come up at once.\NBecause we want people to hear how it really goes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.60,0:11:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and not just in a lecture format.\NI mean, just exactly how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.87,0:11:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd like to sit down?\NYeah, sit down, right there. No, we'll just sit right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.87,0:11:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them sit there and I'll sit here.\NYeah, they need a chair too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.91,0:11:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what's up?\NTwo quick questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.91,0:11:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, can you hear me all?\NThey all want to hear your question.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.00,0:11:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you hear?\NHello?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.11,0:11:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Two quick questions.\NYes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.39,0:11:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scheduled for surgery next week and I'm wondering to know,\Nis having a local or a general anesthetic,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.39,0:11:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is there any spiritual risk associated with that?\NI don't see any spiritual risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.03,0:11:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.03,0:11:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's a great answer.\NSecond thing is I've been suffering, I have constant fatigue
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.03,0:11:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've had it for about the past two years.\NI'm going through the various programs and things you recommend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.03,0:11:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThey still seem to have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.03,0:11:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm just wondering, is there something I'm holding in mind?\NThat's causing me to manifest this fatigue.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.15,0:11:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you tried psychopharmacology?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.15,0:11:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, try it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.15,0:11:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIf you're knocked down all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.15,0:12:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is you can get like spiritually, psychologically depressed.\NThen the neurotransmitters in the brain change.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.15,0:12:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, even though you've solved the original problem,\Nyou can't come out of it because now it's taken on a life of its own
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.15,0:12:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in the brain chemistry.\NSo let's say you go through a tragic thing you've really recovered from,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.15,0:12:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but a couple of years later you're still depressed.\NThat's because your serotonin level or some neurotransmitter got knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.15,0:12:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you just take it briefly, you come out,\Nand then you can taper it off and you don't need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.15,0:12:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So everything is physical, mental, and spiritual.\NIt's all integrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.15,0:12:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't say, well, I just want to do only a spiritual way,\Nbecause if you're really spiritual, you wouldn't resist recovering.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.28,0:12:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NAnd I did tell you that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.28,0:12:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.\NWell, people do because of certain belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.28,0:12:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that's intellectualizing.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.51,0:12:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if I was really spiritual, I wouldn't take Prozac.\NOh, why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.51,0:12:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIf you're spiritual, you would take Prozac.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.51,0:12:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NHow can you serve God when you're depressed and in bed all day?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.51,0:12:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd that's of much use to anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.51,0:12:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.51,0:13:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NSo if you're up and around and being with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So do anything that might help it.\NMaybe just do something mild, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAgain, very brief, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.51,0:13:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I think a lot of times the neurotransmitter goes out.\NYou see, genetically, the human, don't forget,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.51,0:13:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,genetically, you know, about a third of the population,\Nlack sufficient neurotransmitters to not be depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.51,0:13:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,About a third of the population becomes depressed,\Nsometimes seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.51,0:13:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a genetic defect in the human gene pool,\Nand they're depressed for no reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.12,0:13:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's not like your mother got run over by a truck\Nand you're depressed about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.12,0:13:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a reactive depression.\NNo, it's endogenous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.12,0:13:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing happening out there to be depressed.\NThat's why families give them a hard time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.21,0:13:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, well, you've got nothing to be depressed about.\NYou're president of the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.21,0:13:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NYeah, he's thinking about killing himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.21,0:13:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He's very depressed, you know.\NAnd so, you know, denial coming out of pridefulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.21,0:14:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,when we're humble, we accept the limitations\Nof our own physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.21,0:14:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I can't jump six feet high.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.21,0:14:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't jump six feet.\NI couldn't climb that rope in high school,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.52,0:14:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, grade school, or whatever it was.\NSo I'm an ectomorph, and an ectomorph,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.85,0:14:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't climb that rope that fast.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.85,0:14:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.87,0:14:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And then away for one of those strength courses,\Nyou know, Charles something or other.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.87,0:14:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the world champion.\NCharles Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.87,0:14:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles Atlas.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.87,0:14:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is back in the 30s.\NSo I got lesson one, which was free.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.87,0:14:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And then for $6, you could get the whole course.\NWell, $6 in the 30s was, you know, like a thousand now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.87,0:14:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was only one lesson,\Nhow to strengthen your gastrocnemius muscles.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.87,0:14:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did that one over and over.\NI had the greatest gastrocnemius muscles.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.36,0:14:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Later on, I ended up with an 18-mile trip\Nto the paper route, the biggest in Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.36,0:14:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So those little gastrocnemius came around, didn't they?\NOne free lesson, and I had the biggest paper route in town,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.36,0:15:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NSo we don't know what the payoff is on these things, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.39,0:15:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see how you've helped a lot of people,\Nbecause a lot of people out there have the same problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.39,0:15:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.39,0:15:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had denied that opportunity.\NWell, look, people believe it in all these spiritual programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.39,0:15:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Even AA, they'll tell you,\Nwell, you shouldn't take Prozac.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.39,0:15:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?\NYeah, I thought I shouldn't,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.39,0:15:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's why I said to heck with it.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.39,0:15:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So what should I do, kill myself?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.39,0:15:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I kill myself or take Prozac?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.39,0:15:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, death is going to be on your head.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.75,0:15:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would be the advice.\NEverything is physical, mental, and spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.75,0:15:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,including alcoholism and many spiritual things,\Nbecause the body, mind, and spirit are integrated, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.75,0:15:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know through the acupuncture system\Nand the flow of the chi energy and all that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.75,0:15:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're influencing our physiology all the time, you know.\NIn fact, the whole kinesiologic response is based on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.77,0:15:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So every negative thought or feeling is impairing the energy flow\Ndown some acupuncture meridian and impairing some body organ.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.77,0:15:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.77,0:16:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't separate the physical and the mental or spiritual.\NYou know, they interact together almost as one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.77,0:16:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for answering the question.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.89,0:16:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm sure a lot of people out there have had that question.\NIn fact, it does arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.89,0:16:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I see a lot of people in the AA, and that does arise.\NOne of my sponsors says I shouldn't take Prozac.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.89,0:16:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.\NThe question I have is,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.89,0:16:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you say that death is a physical thing.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.08,0:16:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You say that death is...\NOh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.08,0:16:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWe'll put this so that people can hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.08,0:16:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We should put it on .\NWe should put this on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.08,0:16:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat death is predetermined before we're born.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.08,0:16:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I said at the moment of birth.\NOr at the moment of birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.08,0:16:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Moment of birth.\NAnd if that's the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.08,0:16:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,really there is no wrong way to die,\Nand that you can't really kill yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.08,0:16:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then is that correct?\NWhat do you mean, wrong way to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.08,0:16:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the other thing we've found is that\Ndeath is predetermined before we're born.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.08,0:16:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.08,0:16:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.08,0:16:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.08,0:16:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.08,0:16:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.91,0:16:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.91,0:16:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the other thing we've learned so far\Nis that the moment of death is already preset.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.27,0:17:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How you do it is your own choice.\NYou have a big influence on the how of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.20,0:17:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but the time of it, we know, is set.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.15,0:17:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The time.\NSo if you tried to kill yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.16,0:17:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it wasn't your time to go...\NI think...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.68,0:17:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if we've got permission to answer that.\NWe have permission to answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.27,0:17:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we don't have permission to answer that.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.46,0:17:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just trying to figure out...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.46,0:17:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,...then really there's...\NIf it's not our time to go, it doesn't seem like any way could make you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, that's bringing the question.\NIf it wasn't the time to go, how could you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.41,0:17:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NIt's a hypothetical impossibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.41,0:17:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo the problem is how you're phrasing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.27,0:17:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a real question.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.69,0:17:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking me the hypothetical.\NIf a thing wasn't what it is, then how come it isn't something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.15,0:17:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't leave the earth.\NI mean, I can't answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.15,0:17:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say it like a statement.\NYou can't leave the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.15,0:17:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you worrying about it?\NI'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.15,0:18:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just a question because...\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.48,0:18:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just trying to stump the expert.\NIs that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.48,0:18:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.48,0:18:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.48,0:18:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just trying to figure it out because people do kill themselves, and then I'm\Nwondering...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.48,0:18:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBut this is only hypothetical to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.48,0:18:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.48,0:18:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't answer hypothetical questions.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.48,0:18:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI can only answer the real.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.48,0:18:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you thinking about killing yourself?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.48,0:18:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.48,0:18:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got any other questions?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.48,0:18:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnybody got any other questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.48,0:18:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How does...\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.90,0:18:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NMy question is, how does the I am teaching calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.48,0:18:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NAnd how does the Don Hawk teaching calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.66,0:18:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NCan you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NWe're working on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.61,0:18:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI'm going to have to change this over to this side because...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.83,0:18:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.83,0:19:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.24,0:19:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI'll start.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.33,0:19:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a question?\NIn this world, there's 1000 spiritual teachers, techniques, practices, mantras, ashrams, ringing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.19,0:19:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of bells, gongs, incense, robes, shaving one's head, standing on one's head, 20 ways of breathing.\NMillion things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.13,0:19:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we talk about non-duality is we want to avoid all that.\NYou see, if you follow the pathway of strict non-duality...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.44,0:19:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't get embroiled in that, because those are all dualistic.\NNon-duality, you avoid getting sidetracked into the carnival.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.63,0:19:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual carnival out there is endless,\Nand the stuff that comes into my office is so mind-boggling,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.10,0:19:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, nobody would publish this or follow it.\NStrange belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:20:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The more bizarre and strange and non-verifiable,\Nthe more skeptical you have to become.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.59,0:20:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the spiritually committed are notoriously naive and easily taken, I'll tell you.\NAnd some parts of this planet, it has become a great skill over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.07,0:20:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How to fleece the spiritually naive.\NIt's a skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.31,0:20:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's done with masterful techniques,\Nso convincing that hundreds of thousands of people swear this must be a living saint.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.22,0:20:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The great avatar.\NIt's come to rescue mankind, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.08,0:20:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day, I get the name and some book by some great avatar that's come to save mankind.\NThey calibrate 298.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.75,0:20:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can save mankind from 298, I don't know how you do it.\NSo, that's romanticizing, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.19,0:20:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's glamorizing and romanticizing.\NAnd here's the great avatar, you know, the great avatar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.02,0:21:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the next thing is they have many followers.\NWell, don't forget 78% of the population,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.75,0:21:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't forget 78% of the population,\NWell, don't forget 78% of the population,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the population is below 200.\NSo, anybody who's even at 205, if it's already an avatar, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.81,0:21:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To be decided to be honest in a world of crooks makes you almost a Christ, right?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.94,0:21:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, my question is, do every human being come to this earth to grow our consciousness?\NDo every one of us share the same path?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.94,0:21:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my understanding.\NEverybody's here for the same reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.98,0:21:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That we were, if we'd reached absolute enlightenment,\Nthat we're here for the same reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.92,0:21:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for absolute perfection, we'd be in some celestial realm.\NIf we were hopeless, we'd be committed into hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.95,0:21:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If we were hopeless, we'd be committed into hell.\NNo, this is more purgatorial because you see the whole range of opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.95,0:21:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go from saint to sinner at any moment.\NYou can make a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.95,0:21:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The freedom to recover.\NSo, this is to me like a self-healing opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.95,0:22:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, we had good karma to have earned to be in a realm\Nwhere we have the option of undoing our past errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.95,0:22:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our past errors and creating good karma for ourself.\NThe downside of that is you also have the opportunity to create bad karma for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.00,0:22:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go up or down.\NSo to me this is a realm of great freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.44,0:22:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,At any instant you can choose to go up or go down and complete great karmic cycles,\Ngreat karmic cycles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.68,0:22:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this lifetime we see all kinds of transformations in all directions.\NYou look at the immense freedom, you see the immense range here, all the way from the most
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.53,0:22:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,pitiful bottom of the pit to the highest possible levels of enlightenment.\NAll of that is possible here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.33,0:22:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What a great opportunity.\NWhere else could you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.11,0:23:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,People want to come to America because here they see it on an economic level.\NSo we represent the world as more than just economic.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.20,0:23:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's greater than that.\NSo people are attracted to freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.20,0:23:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What we mean by freedom is it's up to your choice to move yourself up or down.\NSo this world offers the maximum opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.95,0:23:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,People want to wipe out something.\NThey're wiping out that as a karmic opportunity because people were counting on that to get
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.63,0:23:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,them out of that last bad karma they had.\NYou got a law of war, now what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.95,0:23:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, you're really stuck.\NSo some clarification.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.95,0:23:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTell me about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.07,0:23:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NThe law of karma specifies that if what we do right now will affect the potential of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.75,0:23:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,choice we can make in the future.\NYes, because of the simple definition, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.22,0:23:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very hard to get beyond the dualistic thinking.\NEverything merely is what it is because it is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.32,0:24:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The sole reason for it being what it is is that it is that.\NTo try and jump that and create an explanation or a rationalization is moving out of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.20,0:24:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It is what it is because that's what it is.\NSo the self-identity is very hard for the mind to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.30,0:24:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It always thinks it is this because of that.\NNo, it is what it is because that is the fulfillment of its potentiality as it is created at this
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.88,0:24:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,instant.\NSo what is the position for free will then?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.76,0:24:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If we just come to here to fulfill our potential?\NWell, because free will operates with limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.89,0:24:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have the free will to be a millionaire by tomorrow, right?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.89,0:24:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo we say we have free will, but the range in which we have free will or options is already
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.39,0:24:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,limited karmically, see?\NYou've become what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.45,0:25:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, what you are now has a certain range of options, and by other choices you\Nmay move yourself into another level where you have a different range of options.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.75,0:25:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A child who's half beaten to death and left to starve and sexually raped and etc. as happens\Nto these young children has no example of love, no experience of love, and it doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.64,0:25:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,have the option to become loving tomorrow, you know?\NNo, you have to put them in a whole field of love, and now they begin to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.79,0:25:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,what that is, be considerate of others, they never thought of being considerate of others.\NYou grab what you want and what you get.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.75,0:25:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And hating others, they don't see anything wrong with that.\NThey come from a world of hatred, so it's only now they begin to experience a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.51,0:25:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,different dimension.\NThey begin to see different options, you know, to let a thing go and not hit the kid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.06,0:25:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,back.\NWow, they never even thought of that, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.86,0:25:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I just feel sorry for the kid instead of hitting him.\NWhoa, what a move.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.34,0:25:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that option wasn't there before.\NSo somehow they have the sufficient karmic momentum to carry them into a therapeutic
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.21,0:26:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and healing environment where they can come out of it and survive, you know, spiritually.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.38,0:26:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you talk about spiritual vision?\NHow do we get that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.38,0:26:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You got one?\NWell I just wanted to tag something on what you were just saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.38,0:26:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's true and this person, like the girl at the girl's ranch, is in this certain\Ncircumstance that she was born into, and in your book you say the average person only
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.38,0:26:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,can move maybe five points in a lifetime.\NThat's the average.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.38,0:26:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Statistical average, yeah.\NYeah, but then I saw on the twelve steps you're talking about somebody moving from
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.97,0:26:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a very low scale to a 540 where healing can happen.\NAnd so I'm wondering, okay, how do you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.47,0:26:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHow do we know what's possible for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.47,0:26:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what I'm really hearing is all things are possible.\NWe don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.28,0:26:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the miraculous is merely completely surrendering to God and then the possible\Nbecomes an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.85,0:26:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is no actual limitation.\NSo is it the person that moved or is it the event that moved?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.16,0:27:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness moves.\NAnd you know, when I said they move five percent, five points in a lifetime, that was just a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.69,0:27:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,statistical average for mankind.\NHow fast does mankind grow?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.69,0:27:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But the individual has no such limitation, you know.\NVery often a person, you can go from the pits of hell all the way up to a state of enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.69,0:27:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in one shot.\NHeaven and hell are a tenth of an inch apart as a fact, and experientially that's precisely
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.39,0:27:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact.\NFrom the pits of hopeless hell, eternal agony, if there is a God, I ask him to help me, suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.56,0:27:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,into the revelation of this divinity itself as the only God.\NThat's what I'm trying to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.74,0:27:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm trying to say.\NThat's what I'm trying to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.74,0:27:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm trying to say.\NThat's what I'm trying to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.74,0:27:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm trying to say.\NThat's what I'm trying to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.34,0:27:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to say that the self as the allness of existence and the personal self went up\Nin smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.92,0:27:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So one can travel hundreds and hundreds of points.\NPeople in these rooms, let's say if we do a before and after, you know, the average
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.85,0:28:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is maybe 10-15 points, something like that.\NBut within the audience, you can say and what was the maximum that any one person jumped,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.48,0:28:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you can probably get a couple hundred.\NSo people go through huge leaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.43,0:28:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the reason...\NDon't forget, for all the people who make a positive choice and advance in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.23,0:28:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,there are a greater number who make a negative choice.\NSeventy percent of the population is choosing to hate the SOB because it deserves it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.89,0:28:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you measure somebody like Carl Jung and he's 5'40, he's 5'40 at that given\Nmoment that he was measured or he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.99,0:28:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I mean, if we ask now, see, don't forget, we're just sketching out.\NIt was just like the telescope was just invented.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.91,0:28:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We're giving a rudimentary idea of the cosmos.\NI'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.25,0:28:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything we're saying is very naive.\NMany of the things that we've discovered, you know, would in themselves just be a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.99,0:28:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,research project.\NFor instance, you watch the evolution of consciousness and how it's spread across the map over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.06,0:29:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can take just minute little, small little things.\NWe don't have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.54,0:29:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just...\NSo we're trying to give a rough scale that you can roughly...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.63,0:29:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're trying to get is a general feeling for consciousness itself and how it grows\Nand what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.30,0:29:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And the awareness that certain spiritual environments are sustaining a spiritual growth and others\Nare deleterious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.93,0:29:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And also what to watch for on the downside.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.24,0:29:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So does karma come from fear?\NIs fear the base?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.24,0:29:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NKarma is a principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.47,0:29:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a principle of consciousness.\NEverything that exists then reflects the quality of its existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.77,0:29:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is outside of time and space.\NSo, when the entity leaves the body, that you take with you, that which you have become,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.76,0:30:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the result of spiritual intention.\NSpiritual intention is what sets your karma and sets your calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.30,0:30:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the intentionality.\NIt's the intention and not the outcome, so we become the consequence of our own spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.74,0:30:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,decisions.\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.74,0:30:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual will sets up karma, not just getting mad because your fingernail broke or the filling\Nstation was closed and it's too late or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.48,0:30:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Those don't change your calibrated level of consciousness because your commitment, whatever\Nyour commitment is, is strong and it doesn't vary from second to second, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.96,0:30:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Major changes will change your calibrated level of consciousness, but it's not aligned\Nwith the trivial from second to second.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.83,0:30:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the decisions you make to forgive instead of to hate.\NAll the twelve steps take you through the evolution of consciousness, to look at myself
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.58,0:31:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the world, to make a decision to do something about it, to admit to myself\Nthat I unaided and lack sufficient power to overcome this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.84,0:31:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So you ask for God's help and understanding and then the miraculous occurs that people\Nsuddenly appear in your life who just seem to have the answers you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.43,0:31:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A five-oh-five dog just happens to show up.\NAll right, it's five after.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.19,0:31:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I just thought we'd try this and if you like it as a teaching technique rather\Nthan a didactic lecture, we'll do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.23,0:31:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can group, more of us group around and I can even go up and down the aisle as long\Nas I've got this thing with me, you know, and we can ask if there's any questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.76,0:31:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think it's a good idea?\NYeah, it's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.76,0:31:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wonderful.\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.76,0:31:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NIt's biblical.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.10,0:31:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, it's real that way.\NSo that's what we're going to do is we're going to try it as a different experience
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.84,0:32:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,collectively.\NYou know, we're all together on this ship at this time and it affects one of us, affects
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.28,0:32:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,us all.\NSo I'm concerned with the happiness and spiritual growth and welfare of everybody here, everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.63,0:32:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,every single person without exception.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.23,0:32:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll reconvene.\NIs this thing on?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.52,0:32:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIs it on?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.50,0:32:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this on?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.75,0:32:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it on?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.72,0:32:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people don't know whether it's on or not.\NThat's not a good sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.95,0:32:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIs everybody here?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.95,0:33:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's here?\NThat's what I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.00,0:33:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NWe had a few questions arise during lunch, a few explanations.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.00,0:33:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to do more gathering together and having informal discussion and have it,\Nyou know, on the sound system.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.24,0:33:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So we all get together.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.61,0:33:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We all get to hear it.\NSome lectures, just the two people up in front are talking to each other and the whole audience
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.86,0:33:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,sits there wondering what's going on.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.03,0:33:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The audience, we calibrate, you know, the audience has gone up 10 points already.\NPeople ask what is the calibrated level of the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.35,0:33:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulties some people have is in correlating the content of these lectures, which is called,\Ndon't forget, devotional non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.38,0:34:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo they come to me with a dualistic question out of a dualistic pathway.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.59,0:34:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning's, can't wait.\NThe lectures calibrate around 980.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.04,0:34:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NWhat is the lecture?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.46,0:34:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The lecture calibrates around 975, 980, 985, 986, 986.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.46,0:34:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're describing a pathway which is extremely advanced.\N985.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.50,0:34:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't always integrate that with a teacher.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.53,0:34:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a teaching that comes out in the 400s, 500s, or 600s.\NBecause it's coming from a different paradigm of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.61,0:34:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the world that we perceive, does it have actual existence?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.61,0:34:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We already cleared that up this morning, that the world that we perceive.\NSo it really brings up the problem of perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.90,0:35:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the positionalities of the ego, we have perceptions and then we presume that\Nour perceptions are the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.46,0:35:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And duality means one transcends all positionalities and begins to see that everything is what\Nit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.42,0:35:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a dramatic jump in consciousness.\NIf you can just see everything is perfectly what it is, period.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.17,0:35:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's putting the period on that is very hard for the mind to take.\NThe mind doesn't want to hear about periods.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.82,0:35:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to go back.\NIt wants to go with why, delve into the hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.61,0:35:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But Baba so-and-so says this, and the course of yuckety-yuck says this, and how is it group\Nsays that?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.80,0:35:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know.\NThat's their problem, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.63,0:36:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a certain teaching that the physical world itself is an illusion.\NAnd the next time you bark your shin, you ask yourself that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.61,0:36:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that this dimension is unreal.\NIt's that it's a different dimension, a different dimension that includes physicality and the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.15,0:36:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experience of physicality.\NWhat is really being meant by somebody like Ramana Maharshi, let's say, is easy to see
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.00,0:36:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from this morning's lecture.\NOnce you stop saying anything about the world, there's nothing to criticize, nothing to correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.53,0:36:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing that needs to be changed.\NYou see that it is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.53,0:36:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This tree is like this.\NThis tree is like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.21,0:36:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This tree is like this.\NThis doesn't mean this is a bad tree or this is a twisted tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.25,0:37:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What many people want to do is take these trees and straighten them out.\NYou hear the snapping of vertebrae as they do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.65,0:37:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Straighten you out so you see it their way.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.78,0:37:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see everything as it is, there's nothing you want.\NThere's nothing you want to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.36,0:37:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't perceive anything as being needful of change.\NYou see each thing being what it is at the moment because each thing is fulfilling its
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.57,0:37:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic destiny and its existence is coming out of divinity.\NThe capacity to move through one's karma into the fulfillment of one's potentiality is the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.15,0:37:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of the enormous field of power which, like gravity, stands there, and in\Nthe power of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.88,0:37:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing goes where it goes by the nature of what it is.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.88,0:38:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing goes where it goes as a consequence of that which it is.\NGravity is not forcing it to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.07,0:38:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To think so is an invention of mentation.\NGravity is just standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.51,0:38:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not doing anything.\NThe little iron filings with their charges and polarities are not really doing anything either.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.76,0:38:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NThey're just automatically shifting in the field as a consequence of that which they
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.88,0:38:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,have become.\NSo the calibrated levels of consciousness are merely how the little charged up iron
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.30,0:38:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,filings filter out.\NJust as you go to the bottom of the sea, each thousand feet down you have a whole different
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.30,0:38:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,dimension.\NAll kinds of systems depend on the pressure of the water being four hundred times that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.38,0:38:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which it is on the surface.\NThere's different consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.53,0:39:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, the sea is not causing it to do that.\NIt's being that as a consequence of the reality in which it is surrounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.61,0:39:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I always forget what these lectures are about.\NSomebody reminded me this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.36,0:39:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It says enlightenment, dedication, goals, and commitment.\NOh, okie doke.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.80,0:39:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we sort of hit that this morning.\NDedication, goals, and commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.80,0:39:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NActually, what happens is the field, you're caught up in the field, and the field brings
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.15,0:40:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you to a greater and greater curiosity, commitment, a certain fraternity with like-minded individuals.\NThe goal is to advance one's consciousness, eventually to reach God, which brings about
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.25,0:40:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a dedication which expresses itself.\NWhich expresses itself as commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.34,0:40:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the commitment eventually becomes more and more intense.\NThere's no linear way to describe it except that if we use the analogy of the sea, the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.30,0:40:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,water pressure becomes enormous depending on the depth.\NAs one gets closer and closer to the surface, transformational changes are the consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.30,0:40:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of the total field.\NSee, it's difficult for people to get out of a dualistic linear causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.61,0:40:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That my dedication is going to cause me to go here and reach that goal.\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.78,0:40:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Reach goal one.\NGot to forgive my mother-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.78,0:41:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.69,0:41:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's more a non-linear subtlety, but it is and can be and eventually becomes extremely\Nintense.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.82,0:41:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes more intense.\NThe desire for enlightenment becomes overriding of everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.42,0:41:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's really the consequence of the field.\NAs you keep surrendering the obstacles, the field gains greater and greater power.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.01,0:41:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And many people have walked away from what the world calls the ultimate, the ultimate\Nof success, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.23,0:41:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate in every department.\NStatus, money, everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.23,0:41:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Power.\NAnd completely walked away from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.65,0:41:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And walked into some little chapel somewhere.\NAnd got the, to me, the top job is the janitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.13,0:42:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The top job is to be the janitor in Shark Cathedral.\NThat's the top job on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.42,0:42:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the congregation and the incense and all clears away, you have the entire cathedral,\Nwhich just knocks you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.92,0:42:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you don't do anything for hours at a time.\NAnd you hire some kid to sweep the floor and dust everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.40,0:42:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you bliss out.\NSo, you can get just so close to the spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.55,0:42:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And then as you get near level 600 or so, there's a tendency to bliss out.\NI have to watch with certain music as they start the music.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.55,0:42:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a certain phrase there where it takes you right through that phase.\NAnd it's just easy to just bliss out and begin to cry and forget the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.94,0:42:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSure, beauty does that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.94,0:43:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It wipes you out.\NSo, the presence of God is sensed as beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.94,0:43:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was a few other questions.\NAnd then I thought, we'll go on to, we'll do sort of like we did this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.94,0:43:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll try it out this time.\NAnd there's a confusion between intention and causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.92,0:43:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality is an operating principle made up by the mind.\NIt calibrates around 460 to explain perceptual phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.92,0:43:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't explain phenomena.\NIt explains one's perception of the phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.92,0:43:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The subtlety of moving from pseudo-objectivity to realizing that everything is subjective,\Nis very, very subtle.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.01,0:44:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And people can study the subject for a lifetime and miss the whole point.\NThat the thought that causality explains things neatly within the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.71,0:44:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,still remains an explanation.\NAnd within that which exists itself, there is no such operational principle as causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.13,0:44:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which would be explicable in terms of physics.\NThe flower is what it is and becomes this potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.96,0:44:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,due to, operationally, an infinite number of factors.\NAnd as we've calibrated in public before,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.07,0:44:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of factors necessary to completely explain\Nwhy one speck of dust is sitting here in the middle of the air
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.07,0:44:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is infinite, infinite, infinite number.\NYou have to have the room here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.40,0:44:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have the very magic pressure.\NYou have to have the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.40,0:44:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have somebody that observed it in the first place.\NAnd for this building to be here, there has to be this state.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.84,0:45:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be this planet.\NThere has to be this galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.84,0:45:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to go back to creation.\NSo the explanation for this piece of dust here
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.84,0:45:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,takes us back to the question of creation itself.\NInexplicable in terms of ordinary consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.78,0:45:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When one first goes into a very advanced state,\None of the strange things,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.59,0:45:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,not in a very, yeah, it's a very advanced state,\Naround 600 or something, high 500s or 600s,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.59,0:45:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere around there,\Nduring the course of miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.59,0:45:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a very not uncommon phenomenon.\NAs you're walking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.69,0:45:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you notice that you're in love with everyone.\NYou begin to notice how everybody looks handsome,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.69,0:45:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody looks well-dressed,\Neverybody looks beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.69,0:45:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is gorgeous,\Nand everything is happening perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.19,0:46:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you also notice that everybody seems\Nto be in a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.67,0:46:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice that people are completely unconscious,\Nthat there's two dialogues going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.67,0:46:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's what they think is being said and happening,\Nand then there's what's really going on
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.67,0:46:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of which they are unaware.\NAnd they seem to be in a dream state.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.80,0:46:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the dream state they're in?\NThis morning we came up with
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.59,0:46:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,what percent of the mind is silent?\N98?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.09,0:46:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo they're unaware of the 98 percent
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.69,0:46:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're so focused on the 2 percent.\NSo focused on the 2 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.90,0:46:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what gives them the dream-like quality.\NThey're like oblivious to what's actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.09,0:46:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what actually is.\NAnd instead they're like focused on the dialogue
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.11,0:46:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 2 percent.\NSo as you go through the course of miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.11,0:47:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as a common experience,\Nor through 10, 12 steps, either one,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.11,0:47:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can reach a state\Nwhere everybody seems to be walking around
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.11,0:47:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,completely unconscious\Nin some kind of a dream state.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.11,0:47:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reality that surrounds them,\Nthey seem to be oblivious, oblivious of.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.11,0:47:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of strange.\NEveryone seems to be asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.11,0:47:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Which tells you to walk around anonymously\Nbecause they don't see who you are
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.11,0:47:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or what you're up to.\NWhich is just loving them,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.69,0:47:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which if they were aware of would scare them\Nand they might call 911.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.69,0:47:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Love frightens people, you know.\NWhen you pull up to the next stop and go light,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.63,0:47:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,look over at the driver at the next car\Nand smile and send him a love.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.92,0:47:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mildred, is that man smiling at me?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.92,0:48:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He's either a lecher or a robber.\NJust try it. It's just fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.07,0:48:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The next stop and go.\NWhoever's in the other car, you look over and...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.03,0:48:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolute consternation.\NYeah, you're gonna be a carjacker or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.42,0:48:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, now there's other questions
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.51,0:48:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that we didn't get a chance to answer this morning.\NDid everything we explained this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.63,0:48:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,seem rather clear and obvious?\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.76,0:48:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, it's a great relief to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.21,0:48:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can experience your own death.\NThe time of death is set anyhow.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.21,0:48:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-eight percent of your mind that you're worried about,\Nthe ego, already doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.25,0:48:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-eight percent of what you thought\Nyou're gonna have to do is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.63,0:48:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You only got two percent left.\NWhat great karmic good fortune
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.17,0:48:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,brings us all here to hear this lecture.\NWhen I discovered it, I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.55,0:49:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, wow, remember?\NWow, everybody's 98% of the way already.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.78,0:49:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that certainly isn't heartening.\NSo, there's only this lingering,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.78,0:49:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,like these little clouds,\Nof the two percent
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.78,0:49:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have to unhook now.\NAnd as we see the mechanism,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.78,0:49:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, once you understand\Nthe nature of a thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.13,0:49:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it begins to dissolve.\NIt begins to dissolve
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.13,0:49:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as you become aware of its nature.\NBecause you're merely holding in place
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.44,0:49:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a perception.\NAnd as you examine what is the reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.57,0:49:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing holding that perception\Nthere anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.57,0:49:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And behind that perception\Nis an intentionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.01,0:49:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There is the payoff to the ego,\Nwhich we didn't recover this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.09,0:49:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because we recovered it before.\NYou say, if all these things
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.17,0:49:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,are what is blocking us from enlightenment\Nand a state of peace and harmony and love,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.17,0:50:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,why would people persist in them?\NBecause all those positionalities
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.28,0:50:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that we looked at\Nall have a payoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.28,0:50:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They all have a payoff\Nin the form of juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.50,0:50:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And to be the victim\Nis so juicy,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.17,0:50:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really hard to give it up.\NTo be right is so juicy,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.23,0:50:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it's hard to give it up.\NRevenge is so juicy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.23,0:50:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, to turn the dagger\Nin the bastard's heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.26,0:50:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's deserved it all these lifetimes\Nand I finally got him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.55,0:50:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NYou look at the Middle East,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.55,0:50:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the glee with which they kill each other.\NLook at the faces on the television.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.55,0:50:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All the young men, man,\Nthrowing rocks at each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.55,0:50:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They're in a state of emotional ecstasy.\NKilling each other for God,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.55,0:50:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jesus, for Allah,\Nwhoever you want to kill them for.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.55,0:50:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever's popular in that culture.\NI mean, just the payoff of that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.50,0:51:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is so enormous.\NTo ask somebody to relinquish it,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.50,0:51:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to relinquish it.\NHow can you get this,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.73,0:51:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,now somebody,\Nto hand over his gun
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.73,0:51:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and become nobody\Nwhen by killing you,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.73,0:51:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he's somebody.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.73,0:51:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The payoff is so enormous.\NAnd so we see that the core of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.92,0:51:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of its stratifications\Nthat we described this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.92,0:51:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is a profound egocentrism.\NThe egoistic core of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.42,0:51:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is what underlies all the things\Nwe described about.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.55,0:51:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ego,\Nbecause it does not live on love,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.55,0:51:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,has to get juiced somewhere\Nand it gets its energy
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.53,0:51:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by juicing negativity.\NThat's how it lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.53,0:51:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some organisms\Nthat live only on dead bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.65,0:52:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And so,\Nthe ego then,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.92,0:52:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is cut off from\Nthat which we might call
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.17,0:52:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the love of divinity,\Nnow, as though it lives in the dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.26,0:52:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,must learn how to suck juices\Nout of that which is negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.51,0:52:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Its subsides,\Nits subsistence,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.03,0:52:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,its source of ongoingness then,\Nis the juice it gets out of negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.03,0:52:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if you ask the ego\Nto let go of the juice,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.21,0:52:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you're asking it to die.\NTry to get somebody to give up
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.15,0:52:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,being the victim.\NGood luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.05,0:52:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way out of it.\NYou watch people on television
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.11,0:52:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,every night.\NThey have made a career
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.11,0:53:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for a lifetime\Njuicing being the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.36,0:53:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're not the victim,\Nyou can make your child the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.82,0:53:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You get strange psychiatric disorders.\NWunschhausen by proxy syndrome.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.82,0:53:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIf you can't be the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.46,0:53:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you become the quasi-victim\Nby having a child as a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.46,0:53:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the degree of pathology\Nto which the ego will resort
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.61,0:53:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to ensure its own survival.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.57,0:53:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see the power\Nof the negativity of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.57,0:53:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the tenacity of it,\Nis the better word,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.57,0:53:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the tenacity with which the ego clings\Nto being right, righteousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.57,0:53:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing others sinful, wrong, and guilty,\Npunishing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.57,0:53:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Punishing them.\NWhy do we want to put somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.59,0:53:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to death for anything?\NPeople get a glee that he deserves it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.59,0:53:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and they punish him.\NThe only trouble with that is
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.86,0:54:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you think people out there deserve\Nis what your unconscious holds for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.55,0:54:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If they should die for it,\Nunconsciously then,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.61,0:54:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,your own fear of death,\Nso you cannot get away with projections.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.67,0:54:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego survives by the paranoid mechanism\Nof seeing evil and all these things out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.82,0:54:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What it thinks everybody out there,\Nthe sentence that it puts on everybody out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.01,0:54:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is the sentence that you've put on yourself.\NIn psychoanalysis, the first rule is,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.80,0:54:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to soften up the superego,\Nthat is the conscience,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.15,0:54:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,before you start bringing stuff up\Nfrom the unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.34,0:54:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because the superego is quite vicious.\NIt wants to execute its enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.44,0:55:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and gloat over the execution.\NExtract every bit of pleasure it can out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.76,0:55:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently,\Nthe homicidal fantasies
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.44,0:55:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which are plunged down into your id,\Nwhich come out of the animal evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.44,0:55:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,an animal doesn't want to,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.44,0:55:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,prevail over the other,\Nhe wants to kill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.44,0:55:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So the unconscious thinks in terms of killing enemies.\NAlright, so,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.57,0:55:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the more we soften the conscience,\Nthen, towards others,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.57,0:55:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we're actually softening it towards ourself.\NThe more we're willing to forgive others,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.57,0:55:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the more we're forgiving towards ourself.\NIn the end, they become one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.57,0:55:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And we become more and more benign.\NSo we ask ourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.07,0:55:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,could I give up the pleasure\Nin watching this guy fry in the electric chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.07,0:56:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of people like to put it on TV and watch it.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.78,0:56:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The macabre, the gruesome\Nof the ego is really immense.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.17,0:56:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the willingness to give up\Nthe payoff of negativity
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.30,0:56:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is what releases it.\NWhen you don't get pleasure
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.84,0:56:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the suffering,\Nwhen you don't get pleasure out of being right,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.84,0:56:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see that everybody is doing the best they can.\NSo forgiveness comes out of the real,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.84,0:56:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the realistic understanding\Nthat everything is only being what it can
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.86,0:56:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time that it's being that.\NSo if the flower is only unfolded at this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.51,0:56:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,should we punish the flower or not?\NCut it off at the stem?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.98,0:56:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should beat it\Nbecause it's a bad flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.98,0:56:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?\NYou begin to see the ridiculousness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.98,0:56:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego's positions.\NAs you do that, you weaken its structure,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.98,0:57:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you start pulling the sticks out.\NThe ego gets weaker and weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.32,0:57:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody in a group like this\Nis farther ahead than what they think they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.32,0:57:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause they focus on the areas
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.32,0:57:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're not pleased with.\NYou know, you're focused on what you're working on.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.32,0:57:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So everybody has a view of themselves\Nas being worse than they actually are.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.32,0:57:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't met anybody who's really awful.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.82,0:57:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are sort of warped individuals\Nwho need help, I'll say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.59,0:57:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A little on the warped side.\NHowever, they can't help being warped.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.69,0:57:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of genes?\NWhat kind of karma?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.69,0:57:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows why they are the way they are.\NSo you end up with a full understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.69,0:57:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason,\Nwe describe all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.69,0:58:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,non-duality,\Nis to transcend the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.98,0:58:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to understand it.\NThe more you understand the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.98,0:58:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the more it begins to collapse.\NAnd you find that compassion is a constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.55,0:58:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It already exists within you.\NJust as devotion already exists within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.71,0:58:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There is already within you\Na well and a reservoir
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.88,0:58:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of intense and powerful devotion\Nthat is far more powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.88,0:58:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,than what you realize yet.\NBecause when the great obstacle arises,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.17,0:58:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,much to your amazement,\Nthere comes out of you an intensity,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.36,0:58:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,an absoluteness\Nthat is willing to walk through anything
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.36,0:58:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach God.\NIt is like the gravity of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.61,0:58:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the closer you get to God,\Nthe more powerful becomes the gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.61,0:58:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the last door,\Nwhere you have to surrender,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.15,0:59:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,very life itself,\Nthe gravity is so powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.15,0:59:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a moment hesitation,\Nthe words of wisdom that you recall
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.38,0:59:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,from some lifetime come to you,\Nand then the trip is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.13,0:59:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you need\Nis already waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.13,0:59:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to have it here.\NIt's like mountain climbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.26,0:59:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you need up there\Nis already sitting up there waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.26,0:59:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to look at yourself and say,\NI don't have within me
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.26,0:59:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what it takes to make this whole trip.\NYou don't have it now,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.26,0:59:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don't need it\Nuntil you get up to this elevation,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.26,0:59:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't need that\Nuntil you get up to this elevation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.26,0:59:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So everything that you need\Nto go the whole way spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.51,0:59:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is already provided for.\NFact. Fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.00,0:59:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to look within yourself and say,\NI don't have that much commitment,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.00,1:00:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have that much drive,\NI don't have that much certitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.00,1:00:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you get to the next block,\Nyou'll suddenly have it,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.21,1:00:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and you turn the corner,\Nyou go down the two blocks,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.21,1:00:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it gets more intense,\Nand so the gravity increases its power.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.32,1:00:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So nobody has to worry about their spiritual evolution.\NIt's already certain.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.86,1:00:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If spiritual evolution wasn't certain,\Nyou wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.13,1:00:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody would be here\Nunless they were scheduled karmically to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.13,1:00:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody else would be here.\NThe very fact that you're here
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.13,1:00:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is a statement of intention and dedication.\NAnd a good 505 is back for a number of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.71,1:00:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be another trip.\NIt's going to go around and answer the questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.80,1:00:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see how it answers questions?\NIt just is what it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.80,1:01:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and the joy of its being what it is\Nreveals to you the absolute truth
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.86,1:01:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're looking for.\NIts joy is coming out of its own existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.96,1:01:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and it shares its joy of existence with you.\NInterestingly,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.96,1:01:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this one asks for nothing in return.\NSo this is like unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.96,1:01:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is love\Nand asks for nothing,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.96,1:01:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't ask you for a pet.\NVery interesting dog
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.28,1:01:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that God sent for the purpose of the lecture.\NSo as I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.30,1:01:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,what you need to explain the thing\Nis waiting for you,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.30,1:01:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so that at the moment\Nwhen you need a dog to demonstrate
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.30,1:01:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're talking about,\Nthe dog appears.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.30,1:01:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NIf only for a dog,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.61,1:01:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,then why not even more so for you?\NOkay, so we realize that we are blessed
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.15,1:01:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,by our being with each other.\NThe other thing I wanted to mention,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.21,1:02:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we're going to go to questions\Nand do it sort of so everyone can hear it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.21,1:02:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd gotten a couple of letters of consternation\Nwhen I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.53,1:02:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it's best to have somebody who knows you\Nrealize that you're on
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.53,1:02:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a seriously committed spiritual path.\NThat person got sort of frightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.53,1:02:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Family, friends,\Nsomebody should realize that,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.71,1:02:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nyou're serious about spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.71,1:02:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And people who get serious about spirituality\Nare known to go into certain
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.71,1:02:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and rather advanced spiritual states\Nwhich are not understood by everybody,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.71,1:02:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,including psychiatrists.\NIt's best to have a spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.88,1:02:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,some spiritually aware friends\Nwho realize what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.88,1:02:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say,\Nyou sit there and begin to meditate,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.88,1:02:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you start surrendering everything as it arises,\None can go in a state of bliss.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.88,1:02:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That is in ecstasy beyond all description.\NNothing's going to get you to come out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.98,1:02:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point,\Nyou need somebody to know,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.98,1:03:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is he blissed out or is he catatonic?\NWe need a psychiatrist or a guru, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.98,1:03:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think in the last book,\NI described how you can tell the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.36,1:03:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with kinesiology.\NIs he in a divine state?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.36,1:03:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIs he catatonic?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.36,1:03:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NOr you may get it the other way.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.94,1:03:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI've had several people tell me
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.19,1:03:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,they were higher than Jesus Christ.\NAnd in the kinesiology, they were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.19,1:03:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll repeat that.\NNobody has ever existed
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.19,1:03:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who's been higher than Jesus Christ\Nor Buddha or Krishna.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.19,1:03:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that tells you\Nthat it has been or is higher than any of them
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.57,1:03:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is not coming from the right place.\NNeeds a psychiatrist, really.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.80,1:03:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Such things do occur.\NAnd, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.86,1:03:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,explain certain rather peculiar phenomena,\Nwhy people are impressed by them.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.86,1:03:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\NI'm not going to justify such statements.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.88,1:03:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That it's a possibility.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.88,1:03:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not a possibility.\NSo if you ever hear it said to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.88,1:03:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,no,\Nyou already know in your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.88,1:04:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is not a possibility.\NAnd by the divination of spirits,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.59,1:04:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we would know that this is not of God.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.03,1:04:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are the only things\NI wanted to make sure I'd said.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.09,1:04:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought,\Nnow we just ask questions
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.19,1:04:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and go do sort of a spiritual free-for-all.\NAnd the way the,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.19,1:04:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the way this is set up,\Nwe're setting up the sound system
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.32,1:04:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so that everybody can hear this.\NWe'll do a little better
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.32,1:04:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and different than this morning.\NWe have a different sound system today
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.65,1:04:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and we finally have it readjusted.\NSo everybody will be able to hear the questions
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.65,1:04:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and hear the answers.\NAnd everyone,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.65,1:04:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I want everybody to feel free\Nto come up and ask anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.65,1:04:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll see what shows up.\NIn a way,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.90,1:04:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we're moving more towards the end of the year\Nwhere we said,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.90,1:04:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it's going to be more and more like that.\NMore and more spontaneous questions dialogue
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.90,1:05:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's actually what's on people's mind.\NIf you don't want to be in the photograph,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.26,1:05:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to be.\NCover your face with a napkin.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.75,1:05:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be photographed with that dog.\NBy the way,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.36,1:05:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,any photographs that are taken\Nare just personal for our scrapbook.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.36,1:05:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing gets put out to the media.\NAnd I just thought you'd like that reassurance
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.17,1:05:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will not appear on the internet tomorrow.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.84,1:05:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I have two questions.\NIn a previous lecture,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.84,1:05:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you had made a statement that about 23% or 24% of the time\Nwe were unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.84,1:05:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you had cautioned people who were into extreme sports.\NCan you elaborate on that?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.26,1:05:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Extreme sports?\NOh, I'm trying to get people used to...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.26,1:05:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, getting out of the Newtonian paradigm,\Nyou have to move through quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.30,1:06:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,where you don't have certainty,\Nyou have probability and likelihoods.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.30,1:06:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The likelihood is\Nif you make 32 high jumps with a five-gainer
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.05,1:06:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're going to make it.\NThe likelihood, the certainty is not there.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.38,1:06:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The 33rd jump, you can break your neck.\NSo I gave an example right here in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.53,1:06:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of nice guys that ran an animal place up there\Nin the back of the Pizza Hut.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.01,1:06:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would...\NWhen you called them,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.21,1:06:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they would come over and get the rattlesnakes.\NAnd they were great.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.23,1:06:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, people are scared of rattlesnakes\Nand a lot of this is becoming sort of suburban in a way.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.23,1:06:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So people just called them\Nand they would come over and get the rattlesnake, no charge.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.23,1:06:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of them got bit 19 times.\NRattlesnakes bit him 19 times.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.01,1:07:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the 20th time, he just assumed he was immune and he died.\NHe was not.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.30,1:07:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, I'm saying don't push your luck\Nbased on the Newtonian paradigm of reality
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.30,1:07:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because the Newtonian paradigm is not the total reality.\NAs we see from quantum mechanics and nonlinear dynamics,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.55,1:07:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're dealing with here is probability and likelihoods,\Nbut not certainty.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.86,1:07:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we have that here.\NIs it too late to put that up?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.86,1:07:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the Newtonian paradigm?\NLet's put that up
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.26,1:07:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because I just wanted to see what I'm saying.\NYou see, once you begin to expand
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.26,1:07:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond the Newtonian paradigm of reality,\Nthis is the Newtonian paradigm of form.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.23,1:07:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's decipherable by the differential calculus.\NSir Isaac Newton was the source of the differential calculus.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.71,1:08:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates in about 460,\Nwhich is the same level as the idea of causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.00,1:08:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a world of certainty,\Nlinear certainty.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.53,1:08:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's certain because of the limitation of its own self-definition.\NAs you begin to move to the next higher level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.60,1:08:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,now you're dealing in quantum mechanics,\Nquantum reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.60,1:08:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, in the Newtonian,\Nthis causes this and there's an absolute certainty about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.85,1:08:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's only the macroscopic world.\NIn the microscopic world now,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.43,1:08:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of quantum mechanics,\NE equals MC squared,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.50,1:08:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you start going from\Nthe Schrodinger equations,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.56,1:08:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,time independent and time dependent.\NYou're going through the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.56,1:08:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're ending up with the Dirac conclusion.\NAnd through the von Neumann processes,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.56,1:09:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A or B, one or two,\Nwhat you have now is you don't have certainty
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.77,1:09:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,at the submicroscopic level.\NYou have probability.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.77,1:09:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we talk in spiritual language\Nabout the influence of the field,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.77,1:09:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're talking about now\Nis not causality on a one-to-one linear basis,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.77,1:09:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the field.\NLet's say if you have a drinking problem,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.77,1:09:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,if you just go to AA and sit in the room,\Nthe field begins to alter your thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.77,1:09:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a predictable world.\NIf this is the way the world is,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.14,1:09:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,after 19 rattlesnake bites,\Nyou'd be okay on the 20th.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.47,1:09:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That isn't the way the world is.\NThis is the way the world is.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.47,1:09:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Likelihood.\NIt's likely that 19 out of 20 times,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.47,1:09:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the 20th time you'll make it.\NYou see, in the quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.78,1:09:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,this linear certainty is beginning to loosen up\Nnow a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.78,1:10:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is 100 times out of 100 times.\NThis is 99.9% out of 100 times.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.92,1:10:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you begin to see disorderly, illogical,\Nunpredictable, free, creative.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.92,1:10:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got space for free will.\NIf this is Newtonian,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.01,1:10:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be no karmic merit in any decision\Nbecause this caused you to think this way,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.01,1:10:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that caused you to think this way,\Nand that's what caused you to make this conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.01,1:10:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No room for karmic merit.\NNo spiritual freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.13,1:10:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be room for the unpredictable,\Nthe illogical, to be free, to be creative,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.13,1:10:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,imaginative, progressive.\NYou see, this field is diffuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.13,1:10:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's diffuse.\NIt's not causal.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.31,1:10:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not local.\NThis world is provable.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.07,1:10:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This world is comprehensible,\Nbut not provable.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.35,1:10:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I get oddball letters all the time from people\Nthat get lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.61,1:10:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They miss what the whole book's about,\Nand they start to argue with the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.61,1:11:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,mathematical analogies that I make.\NI think I made it quite explicit.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.61,1:11:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,These are just analogous.\NThey're not literal.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.61,1:11:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And they start to argue about provability.\NYou can't actually prove anything
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.68,1:11:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,any time except something that you mentalize.\NNothing in reality can be proven.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.68,1:11:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's called provable is a mentalization.\NIt's provable within a structured mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.17,1:11:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not provable within the world\Nbecause causality doesn't exist within the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.17,1:11:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so you couldn't prove it because it isn't there.\NIt's a conception.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.28,1:11:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can comprehend it,\Nbut you cannot prove it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.28,1:11:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's observable.\NEverything is simultaneous.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.28,1:11:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Past, present, and future are not sequential.\NIn the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.28,1:11:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that was yesterday, now is now,\Nand there's tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.73,1:12:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In the microscopic world,\Ntomorrow has already happened,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.73,1:12:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and yesterday won't get here till tomorrow.\NThe reason everybody's here is because of their future.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.85,1:12:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They think they're propelled by their past.\NPeople are attracted because their future
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.31,1:12:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,has already been decided.\NIf your future hadn't been decided to become enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.50,1:12:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be no reason for your body\Nto drag itself here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.22,1:12:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Like an electromagnet,\Nyou're being pulled by the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.22,1:12:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not being propelled by the past.\NThe past is over already,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.06,1:12:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so where would it get the power to propel you?\NThe past is already dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.80,1:12:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's dead,\Nhow would it be activating you in the present?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.80,1:12:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, it's not.\NWe said time-dependent and time-independent.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.56,1:12:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the two Schrodinger equations.\NStochastic meaning unpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.63,1:12:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unlimited.\NYou see, it's altered by observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.63,1:13:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the Heisenberg principle.\NAs we explained before,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.61,1:13:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein calibrates at 499.\NThis is where he bucked.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.17,1:13:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He bucked right here because he said,\Nafter the Copenhagen Convention,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.22,1:13:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,he said,\NI prefer to think that there is an independent,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.22,1:13:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,objective universe independent of human consciousness.\NBecause the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.56,1:13:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,forces you to a metaphysical,\Nphilosophic shift,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.61,1:13:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole basis of science,\Nand it requires a shift of paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.93,1:13:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,At calibration level 500,\Nyou move from the literal,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.93,1:13:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,provable Newtonian paradigm\Ninto the non-provable subjectivity
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.93,1:13:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual reality.\NAnd Einstein just refused to go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.77,1:14:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He refused to go there.\NAt the same time, he was quite religious.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.06,1:14:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite religious, and yet,\Nnot yet ready to make a paradigm jump.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.60,1:14:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That there is a reality\Nthat is not objective, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.85,1:14:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but subjective.\NSo, this then becomes unlimited.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.60,1:14:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You see possibilities.\NSo, the fact that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.60,1:14:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's altered by observation,\Nthe only thing that intervenes,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.60,1:14:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,intervenes in the two,\Nbetween the Schroeder and the Dirac equation,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.60,1:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is the Heisenberg principle of observation.\NOnce you've really looked at it,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.60,1:14:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,once human consciousness has touched it,\Nit's already changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.60,1:14:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already changed.\NYou've collapsed the wave function.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.63,1:14:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And because you've collapsed the wave function,\Nyou have altered
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.63,1:14:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective consciousness of all of mankind.\NEvery time everybody here says yes
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.21,1:14:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to something that's integrous\Nand no to something that's not integrous,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.21,1:14:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you've made it more and more difficult\Nfor the non-integrous
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.21,1:15:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue the way it is.\NSo, the field, as it moves from 190
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.27,1:15:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,back in 1980,\Nsuddenly shifted to 207.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.27,1:15:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The total field of human consciousness\Nwill not tolerate now
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.59,1:15:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,things that it tolerated when I grew up.\NWhen I grew up,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.77,1:15:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,if you didn't get their money,\Nsomebody else will.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.77,1:15:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they told me.\NGet their money,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.77,1:15:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't get them,\Nsomebody else will.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.77,1:15:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, this is not integrous.\NYou know, this old farmer's
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.77,1:15:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,never going to get his money back\Nout of the peanut vending machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.77,1:15:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, if you don't get their money,\Nsomebody else will.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.52,1:15:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That went back in the 50s\Nor whenever that time was.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.86,1:15:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't go now.\NIt wouldn't go now
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.86,1:15:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because after Enron and all that\Nand Martha Stewart and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.86,1:15:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,people now see that integrity\Nis what you're going to be nailed up there for,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.86,1:15:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,friends, not profit, integrity.\NI mean, they made plenty of profit.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.86,1:15:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They should have been\Na Fifth Avenue ticker-tape parade for them,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.86,1:15:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,these guys that made billions\Nfor all the investors.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.89,1:15:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, their heads rolled.\NSo, the world has shifted.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.89,1:16:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, every time we are integrous,\Nwe increase the likelihood that integrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.89,1:16:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood that integrity\Nis going to be continued.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.85,1:16:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can see you're dealing with uncertainty\Nand, of course, the difference is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.85,1:16:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you're dealing with power.\NHere, you're dealing with force.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.85,1:16:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you're dealing with content.\NHere, you're dealing with context.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.85,1:16:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is the context,\Nthe field out of which the power is coming,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.85,1:16:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is the content or form.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.50,1:16:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,all spiritually evolved people\Nor spiritually committed people
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.50,1:16:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by the sheer commitment\Nis they are already in the process
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.50,1:16:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of changing the world.\NPeople say,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.50,1:16:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what can I do to change the world?\NI tell them, stay out of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.76,1:16:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Say your prayers, stay out of trouble.\NYou're doing a lot for the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.76,1:16:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Seventy-eight percent of the world\Nis doing otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.76,1:16:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not doing what they can for each other\Nor for the world, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.76,1:16:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I try to teach the girls\Nthat the girls aren't, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.76,1:17:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one little smile\Nwill change somebody else's whole day.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.76,1:17:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know,\Nif you want to be surrounded by love,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.89,1:17:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all you have to do\Nis acknowledge people
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.89,1:17:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as you walk through the day.\NYou know, you say thank you,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.02,1:17:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and the telephone operator,\NI said, boy, you really took that order.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.02,1:17:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That was terrific.\NYou can just hear them light up.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.02,1:17:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They just light up.\NSo, they're sort of like the dog, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.34,1:17:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When you give it a pat,\Neverybody just blossoms.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.34,1:17:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so simple.\NAnd that's why New York
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.34,1:17:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is a wonderful and friendly place.\NBecause as you smile,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.34,1:17:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,literally walking down the street,\Nthey just go,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.34,1:17:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that little flower just blossoms,\Nand you become part of the conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.35,1:17:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which allow them to blossom.\NOkay, so that sort of cuts.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.38,1:17:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you asked that.\NAren't you sorry?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.38,1:17:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll shut this off.\NShe said she's sorry she asked.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.69,1:17:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.\NNext question.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.53,1:18:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As a participant in the health field,\Nand being in a very evidence-based period,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.77,1:18:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,am I adding negatively\Nto the collective unconscious effect
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.77,1:18:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,on disease process?\NOn what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.77,1:18:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm making wrong assumptions,\Nbut my understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.77,1:18:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of the collective unconscious\Non disease processes
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.81,1:18:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is that our diseases,\Na lot of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.81,1:18:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,are the result of the collective unconscious.\NWell, certainly,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.81,1:18:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the kind of disease that we're dealing with\Nis not the disease that we're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.81,1:18:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the disease that we're dealing with.\NIt's certainly the kind of disease that we see.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.81,1:18:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the miracle says,\Nyou're subject to what you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.81,1:18:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you think smoking's gonna kill you,\NI advise you not to smoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.81,1:18:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You have stopped smoking, haven't you?\NOh, definitely.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.35,1:18:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you.\NI haven't started.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.35,1:18:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go on to the next person.\NGo ahead,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.35,1:19:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because you had a couple questions.\NWe've got to get another.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.35,1:19:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,People ask that question, you know?\NYou're subject to what you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.82,1:19:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you may have already answered this,\Nbut...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.85,1:19:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's time to leave, you leave,\Nand many people with pure lungs
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.78,1:19:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,leave this planet every day.\NIf bad lungs don't get you out,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.53,1:19:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,karma will find another way,\Na CVA or a stroke or, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.53,1:19:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the moment arrives,\Nyou will not be here afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.06,1:19:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you may have already answered this,\Nbut if in amongst all those ego messages
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.06,1:19:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there is this sensation\Nof wanting to transcend that,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.06,1:19:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that can't be coming,\Nthat message of wanting to transcend the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.25,1:19:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,can't be coming from the ego,\Nis that coming from...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.25,1:19:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit, yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.43,1:20:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, like a field of gravity,\Nthis field is like attracting,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.43,1:20:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,pulling us towards it.\NAnd meantime, the ego is struggling
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.97,1:20:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to prevent that from happening.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.97,1:20:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as you transcend it,\Nthat's the death of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.97,1:20:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the end.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.97,1:20:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And it loses its grip on mankind.\NSo, as you try to move up,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.10,1:20:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it tries to counter it, you know,\Ntries to counter it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.10,1:20:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get back.\NThe more you understand it,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.19,1:20:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the weaker it becomes.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.19,1:20:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,See, it's not operating in the dark.\NAnd light and dark are not opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.02,1:20:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see,\Nas you hold the light on something,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.02,1:20:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the darkness disappears.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.02,1:20:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because darkness is not the opposite of light,\Nit merely is its absence.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.02,1:20:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the calibrated scale of consciousness then,\Nthe degree to which divinity and love predominate
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.22,1:21:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is why the calibrations are high.\NThe more it tends...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.34,1:21:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The more the light goes down,\Nthe more towards darkness,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.34,1:21:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the lower end of the scale.\NBut they're not opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.34,1:21:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The top is not the opposite of the bottom of the scale.\NSo, it's just a gradation.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.34,1:21:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, every conscious decision we make then\Nmoves us up and down in the water,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.34,1:21:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,like little quarks, you know.\NI always figured like little quarks
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.34,1:21:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with little things like this.\NAnd when we go this way,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.34,1:21:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the quark goes up.\NAnd when we go this way,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.34,1:21:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the quark goes down.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.34,1:21:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...\NBut what's making those choices?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.34,1:21:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the field making those choices,\Nthis desire to transcend,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.34,1:21:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or is it the ego making the choices?\NThe spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.34,1:21:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit's making the choices.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.34,1:21:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you a health-related question, too?\NIf the goal is to completely surrender,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.47,1:21:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as you were talking about\Nwhen you were going through
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.47,1:21:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the 12 steps,\Nthen aren't efforts of searching around,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.47,1:21:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for healing kind of things\Nsort of resisting that?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.47,1:21:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Resisting having completely surrendered,\Nif it is in my karma
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.47,1:22:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a particular physical condition?\NWell, it's sort of an ambiguous question
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.47,1:22:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because the intention to get well\Nwould lead you to seek out the means to do so,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.47,1:22:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,which would be the natural thing to go.\NThe capacity to completely,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.63,1:22:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,totally surrender\Nand allow it to be however it is
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.63,1:22:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,would be a different level of consciousness.\NAnd a higher level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.92,1:22:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it persists or does not persist,\Nis irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.92,1:22:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a choice?\NThat would be a choice,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.92,1:22:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but you see,\Nat this level is yes,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.92,1:22:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,at this level is no,\Nat this level is yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.92,1:22:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to know in what context,\Nwhat calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.92,1:22:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you're arriving at this decision.\NBecause at one level,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.05,1:22:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't make any difference\Nwhether you live or you die.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.05,1:22:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.07,1:22:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's how it seems from that level.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.07,1:22:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But it makes a difference to whom,\Nwhether you live or die,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.07,1:22:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera.\NSo one constantly chooses life
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.27,1:23:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in whatever form it may express itself,\Nincluding the non-physical.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.27,1:23:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say,\Nit was time to leave the body, goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.46,1:23:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And one function I used to have in the nursing home\Nis I would say to some old lady
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.46,1:23:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with all these tubes stuck in her,\Nand she'd be going up and down the wheelchair,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.46,1:23:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,saying,\Nhelp,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.46,1:23:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,help,\Nhelp,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.77,1:23:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,help.\NAnd they're putting more tubes in her
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.77,1:23:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and more things,\Nand she must need more narcotics.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.77,1:23:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said,\Nwhat do you want help with?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.77,1:23:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She said,\Nlet me go,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.77,1:23:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,let me go.\NNobody lets her die.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.77,1:23:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's against Medicare rules.\NDo you know it's against Medicare rules
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.77,1:23:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to let anybody die?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.64,1:23:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt's against Medicare rules.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.64,1:23:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's illegal to let anybody die.\NThe most natural thing in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.64,1:23:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to get born,\Nto die,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.64,1:23:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the two things that are inevitable,\Nis against the Medicare rules.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.64,1:23:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What she means by help is let me out of here.\NThey won't let me die.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.78,1:23:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the natural end of life?\NThe natural end of life
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.78,1:24:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is you reach a certain feeling of inevitability.\NAnd at that point,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.78,1:24:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you have no interest in eating anymore.\NThe natural way to leave the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.78,1:24:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is to realize that and to stop eating.\NThat's nature's way.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.78,1:24:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When the animal gets sick enough,\Nit goes off,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.78,1:24:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it wants solitude,\Nit wants to stop eating,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.78,1:24:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and be left alone in peace\Nto slowly let itself out of there.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.78,1:24:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And this poor old lady is pleading for that.\NPlease put me somewhere in the corner
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.78,1:24:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and leave me alone\Nand stop trying to hydrate me,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.94,1:24:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,tube feed me,\Net cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.94,1:24:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and let nature take its course.\NThe natural way to leave is to stop eating.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.94,1:24:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NIf anybody says they want to die and commit suicide,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.21,1:24:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say,\Nhow was lunch?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.21,1:24:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very good.\NThey're right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.92,1:25:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been working on,\Nthank you,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.92,1:25:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on spiritual realization for the last three years,\Nand I have gotten to the point
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.92,1:25:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that I understand that there is no causal,\Nthat it isn't my past.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.92,1:25:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't blame anyone or anything that happened,\Nand I do see the unfolding and the blossoming.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.92,1:25:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When I start thinking about the past,\Nsometimes I don't think about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.92,1:25:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I do,\NI have to kind of think
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.92,1:25:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've really firmly put it behind me.\NBut in your last book,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.92,1:25:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you said that it can be an advantage\Nto have past life regression
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.92,1:25:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to find out what the karmic residual is\Nthat is causing the things to happen in your life
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.92,1:25:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you better understand.\NIf you're up against a block,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.92,1:25:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a block,\Nand you can't seem to overcome it,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.68,1:25:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and you try prayer,\Nyou try everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.90,1:25:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nit's usually something specific.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.93,1:25:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And, yeah, past life recall,\Npast life regression can sometimes,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.93,1:25:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,well, sometimes take it right there.\NAnd there's very simple techniques,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.93,1:26:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,just self-hypnosis.\NYou get off at floor 18,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.93,1:26:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of a sudden,\Nall of a sudden the movie starts,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.93,1:26:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and only it's you in the movie.\NAnd it's quite obvious now
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.93,1:26:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what the whole story is about,\Nand what you suspected is not only so,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.93,1:26:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's very, very so.\NAnd each of those lifetimes,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.93,1:26:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do past life regression,\Nas you come to in that lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.93,1:26:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it's always you that's there.\NSo you had experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.93,1:26:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always the same me each time.\NThere he is, a blacksmith.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.03,1:26:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In that lifetime,\Nhe's got huge muscles like that,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.03,1:26:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's got an apron,\Nand he's a very powerful guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.03,1:26:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a very strong guy.\NSo each lifetime that one recalls.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.22,1:26:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's only certain critical ones\Nthat are of any, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.22,1:26:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic consequence\Nthat tend to come in people's minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.42,1:26:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But it sometimes solves self-possession,\Nself-pity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.42,1:26:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why me?\NWhy this pattern?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.48,1:26:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the usual answer is\Nbecause it's exactly, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.48,1:27:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you're playing the other role now.\NAnd many a person says, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.57,1:27:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I must have been an SOB in another lifetime.\NWell, I'll tell you, that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.68,1:27:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You were an SOB in other lifetimes.\NThe other thing I would like to say
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.68,1:27:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is about the 12 steps I did.\NI was an alcoholic,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.68,1:27:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I did use the 12 steps.\NAnd a lot of the things that,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.68,1:27:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I did stop drinking.\NI'm very thankful to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.68,1:27:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was very much giving over\Nthe idea that I had no power over it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.68,1:27:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I basically answered my own question\Nthat what you were going through
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.68,1:27:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is that all I have to do now\Nis surrender the rest of the blocks to,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.68,1:27:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to continue that.\NI think I stopped 15 years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.47,1:27:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,when I stopped drinking.\NI stopped to continually take that inventory.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.47,1:27:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think now that if I just more surrender myself\Nto the idea,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.47,1:27:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have to go through the past life regression.\NYeah, because, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.47,1:27:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of people, let's say,\Nif they have,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.47,1:28:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,if they belong to something like AA,\Nwhere the sobriety indicates sort of an endpoint,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.47,1:28:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then they may just maintain the program.\NBut Bill Wilson, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.67,1:28:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,said that the AAs don't really realize\Nthat the 12 steps,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.67,1:28:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that sobriety is just the,\Njacks for openers.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.67,1:28:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's jacks for openers.\NYou do the steps, you get sober.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.67,1:28:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And most people think,\Nwell, I'm done now.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.67,1:28:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, no,\Nthat's what leads to the great discoveries
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.67,1:28:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the great spiritual growth and experiences.\NSo he used to think that was maybe an error
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.53,1:28:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that they should not have indicated\Nthat sobriety itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.53,1:28:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,although I think for practical reasons,\Nthat's good enough for this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.53,1:28:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing one excellent job today.\NIt's okay to do a wrestling point
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.53,1:29:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for a lifetime or two\Nand then start up your momentum again.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.13,1:29:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Kind of a follow-up to that is,\Ncould you expand a little more
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.06,1:29:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,on a technique for accessing previous lives?\NI don't do past life regression.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.31,1:29:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's a very simple thing.\NI can tell you how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.43,1:29:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You just do self-hypnosis.\NYou know how to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.43,1:29:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.81,1:29:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So you got to go learn self-hypnosis.\NAnd you have to ask,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.81,1:29:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,what is your motivation?\NIs it worth?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.81,1:29:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it may be.\NAnd first of all,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.81,1:29:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize that one is at a certain point\Nin a continuum of an endless series,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.05,1:29:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,an endless life, actually.\NIt's just one life.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.05,1:29:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's these various chapters and episodes.\NEach one you dip into the physicality
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.05,1:29:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,as a very definite karmic purpose.\NYou see it quite clearly.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.05,1:29:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the next lesson comes around.\NSo there's a certain benefit to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.05,1:30:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's people who have written books on it.\NThey're accessible.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.05,1:30:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the names of them.\NIt's primarily self-hypnosis
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.05,1:30:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and then your intention, intentionality.\NYou hold in mind a certain intentionality
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.05,1:30:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and you walk down the dark steps.\NAnd you take the elevator
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.18,1:30:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and you find your answer on level eight.\NYou get off the elevator
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.18,1:30:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the whole lifetime begins,\Nexperientially.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.27,1:30:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like you're watching a movie\Nwhere that's happening there.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.27,1:30:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the movie\Nand everything moves around you as it did.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.27,1:30:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're, I mean, the self is there.\NIt's very much like out-of-body experience
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.93,1:30:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you go out of body.\NIt's very much you that's out of the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.84,1:30:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The physicality is there,\Nbut the you is here.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.84,1:30:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, there's techniques\Nusing out-of-body experience
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.06,1:30:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for karmic research.\NBecause you go in realms
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.06,1:31:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,where there is no past, present, or future\Nand you merely go back and visit.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.06,1:31:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's...\NWho wrote Journeys Out of the Body?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.77,1:31:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Monroe, yeah.\NMonroe Institute.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.47,1:31:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Various places like that.\NSo with a little inquiry,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.47,1:31:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you can find places that specialize\Nin past life recall
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.47,1:31:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and various techniques,\Nhypnosis, out-of-body experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.47,1:31:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thanks.\NMy 2% is very active.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.47,1:31:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And...\NAnd I keep getting to this point
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.51,1:31:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,where I think,\Nwhy isn't this just maybe
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.51,1:31:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the ultimate ego trick, all this,\Nand that we're all experiencing
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.51,1:31:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the same ultimate ego trick?\NWell, that is a psychiatric problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.06,1:31:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I can go sit on that.\NAnd the answer comes to you
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.06,1:31:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,just out of nowhere.\NSo you're looking somewhat,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.22,1:32:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like you're pressing the linear.\NYou're trying to press logic, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.22,1:32:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's not going to work\Nin the spiritual domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.22,1:32:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more your intention to know,\Nyour prayer and dedication, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.22,1:32:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,will finesse.\NSo you see in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.22,1:32:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm,\Nyou cause things to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.22,1:32:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In the spiritual paradigm,\Nit's more like you finesse them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.22,1:32:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Through prayer and meditation,\Nyou increase the likelihood
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.27,1:32:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that when you get your gas\Nat the next station,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.75,1:32:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the guy giving you the change says,\Nand by the way, so-and-so,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.75,1:32:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's just what you're asking for.\NSo you have to be open
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.75,1:32:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to hear the answer to the question.\NAnd they'll come through, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.06,1:32:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and just sit next to somebody on a bus,\Nand he looks from this paper,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.06,1:32:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and he says, yackety-yack,\Nand man, that's just what you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.06,1:32:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So you give the universe a chance\Nto respond to your question.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.97,1:32:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't look for a linear cause and effect.\NBecause once you pose the question out there,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.00,1:33:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer will come back to you.\NYeah, somebody will just walk up to you
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.81,1:33:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, yackety-yack,\Nand you say, whoa, hey, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.14,1:33:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is about prayer.\NSo when people say they're praying for me,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.52,1:33:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,should I worry about that?\NThat's a good sign.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.90,1:33:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So really, what is prayer,\Nor how would we best pray?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.97,1:33:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, prayer, yes.\NYou see, through devotion and dedication,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.22,1:33:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,one's commitment to God becomes quite intense.\NAnd you see, in the 12 steps,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.97,1:33:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it addresses prayer directly.\NSought through prayer and meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.97,1:33:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to increase our conscious contact with God.\NSo you're like permitting,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.02,1:34:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you're taking,\Nyou see, the ego is very much yang,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.15,1:34:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,papo,\Nand the spirit is very much yin,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.89,1:34:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing.\NSo it's hard for those who live in a world
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.47,1:34:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of the harder you push,\Nthe harder you try,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.47,1:34:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater you bring home the bacon, you know?\NSo spiritual work is more like yin,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.10,1:34:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you get out of the way of it\Nand you float back with it,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.46,1:34:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the answer comes to you.\NIt comes to you out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.01,1:34:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer came out of nowhere\Nthe other day driving along.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.22,1:34:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, what's the best way\Nto present a certain piece of material?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.35,1:34:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it was just obvious.\NNot question and answer, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.57,1:34:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I posed the question at breakfast\Nand at noon I'm driving along
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.82,1:34:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and the answer just revealed itself.\NSo you learn how to finesse using yin.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.85,1:35:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So the power of yin is equal to the power of yang.\NIt doesn't get the publicity.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.35,1:35:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nuclear submarines get the publicity.\NNo, it's the power of yin that summons forth
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.55,1:35:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is needed for survival, see?\NSo that's the power of prayer,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.51,1:35:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it summons to itself,\Nsummons, attracts to itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.60,1:35:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any such thing\Nas praying for another person?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.93,1:35:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.\NPeople pray for each other all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.60,1:35:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear God, please let them see the right way to go.\NWe all, we pray that God's will be done, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.97,1:35:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That God's will be done.\NWe ask for what is God's intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.97,1:36:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because if a person is going through a karmic lesson\Nand you want to interfere with the karmic lesson,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.18,1:36:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you're destroying the person's spiritual integrity.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.18,1:36:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So if people get sober because you have them arrested and jailed\Nand put in prison and then into a forced program,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.18,1:36:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,there's really no karmic benefit.\NHe hasn't said yes to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.61,1:36:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NIt did not come of his own volition through his own surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.61,1:36:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So that sobriety will last till he gets out of jail, you know,\Nand on the way home it'll disappear because it's forced.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.65,1:36:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no karmic merit.\NSo the first step in the Al-Anon program, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.65,1:36:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is in a way saying,\Ndon't try to rob others of karmic merit
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.65,1:36:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,by acting, you know, in what you think is their best interest\Nusing force and coercion.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.65,1:36:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it's saying.\NAllow people to derive the karmic benefit
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.51,1:36:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes only from saying,\NI surrender to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.51,1:37:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask God for help.\NYeah, I ask God for help.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.27,1:37:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a totally different thing.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.39,1:37:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd some people that are forced to, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.64,1:37:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,discontinue certain behaviors may also shift later on\Nand now do it by agreement and understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.81,1:37:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So maybe they're forced to go there by the court,\Nand then much to their surprise,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.81,1:37:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they become enthusiastic about it, you know?\NI have a question that I'm having a little bit of problems wording it,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.65,1:37:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think you'll pick up real quick.\NThroughout the history of mankind or humankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.72,1:37:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we have avatars and the great enlightened ones,\NKrishna, Buddha, Jesus, as you've mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.81,1:37:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I would assume that there have been females\Nthat have reached these levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.81,1:38:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the answer is no.\NThe question is politicizing it, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.63,1:38:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the reason I was asking, no, my thinking is,\Nwas that perhaps there were,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.63,1:38:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but because of the nature of the civilization,\Nthey weren't recognized.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.78,1:38:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been able to detect it,\Nbut the minute I am, I will announce it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.55,1:38:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The other question was,\Ngoing through the dark night of the soul,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.73,1:38:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which you relate to about the agony,\Nthe emotional and mental agony,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.73,1:38:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,how does one discern that between an ego conniption fit?\NWell, the ego can take you places.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.72,1:38:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,One is transformative and the other is not.\NThe dark night of the soul takes you to,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.97,1:39:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the resolution to it is a spiritual experience,\Nwithout which that likely would not have happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.53,1:39:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you've answered my question, thank you.\NThe question about men and women,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.14,1:39:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as being God,\Nthe question, because we've asked it,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.92,1:39:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to do with the strength of the nervous system,\Nthat to go over 600, to go over 700 especially,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.23,1:39:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is extremely difficult for the human nervous system.\NAnd what we got is,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.97,1:39:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the only reason that men go the whole way,\Nstatistically more than women,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.17,1:39:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is because the nervous system\Nis sufficiently strong to handle.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.17,1:39:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I got.\NAlthough I bet you're going through childbirth,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.17,1:39:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine that women don't have an equal...\NI was so glad I wasn't born a woman, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.17,1:40:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They go through and survive a lot.\NSo I think we can ask it again,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.17,1:40:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has nothing to do with gender.\NIt has to do with nervous system.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.17,1:40:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer I give is permitted.\NThe answer I give is correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.17,1:40:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only because of the nervous system.\NFor the same reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.17,1:40:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,moving rocks is usually given to men to do,\Nrather than women, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.17,1:40:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBecause you...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.17,1:40:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I...\NYeah, I'm live.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.17,1:40:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk, and we all are aware of Mother Teresa\Nand the tremendous ability that she had to do what she did.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.17,1:40:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just thought, perhaps,\Nmaybe there's some other females in history
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.30,1:40:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm not aware of.\NThere's a great many Christian saints.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.30,1:40:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, Saint Teresa of Avila,\Nmany...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.30,1:40:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Many Christian saints that were women.\NAnd, you know, in our lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.68,1:40:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother Teresa calibrates over 700.\NI mean, that's about as good as you can get on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.89,1:41:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarely, rarely ever does calibration ever go over 700.\NAnd if it does, you don't...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.97,1:41:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, as each level is reached,\Nyou don't hear from them.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.97,1:41:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600, you won't hear from...\N50% of them are going to leave,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.97,1:41:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because you don't have to breathe,\Nyou don't have to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.97,1:41:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize that...\NYour reality...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.97,1:41:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the point of, you know,\Nto please your relatives breathing this body again?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.97,1:41:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So 50% of the time, they don't do it.\NAnd then as you get higher to the 700s or 800s,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.15,1:41:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,hardly any of them come back in the world.\NAnd when you get beyond that,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.64,1:41:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it's once in a number of centuries\Nthat anybody will persist.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.64,1:41:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I got my answer.\NWomen are smart enough they don't come back
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.64,1:41:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as often as men do.\NThey got the brains to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.06,1:41:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't disagree with you.\NThey're too smart.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.89,1:42:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Who needs this?\NBye.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.72,1:42:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.\NI think I have the answers to these questions,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.36,1:42:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but I also think I might be intellectualizing,\Nso that's why I want to present this to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.36,1:42:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I, too, am an ex-drunk,\Nand I work the steps,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.36,1:42:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and amazing things happen as a result.\NAnd I listened to your tape
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.36,1:42:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,on alcoholism and consciousness,\Nand if I understood you correctly,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.36,1:42:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,your theory behind that was\Nfor those of us that are alcoholic,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.65,1:42:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason why we drink\Nis because we're actually addicted
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.65,1:42:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to the God experience that we get through alcohol,\Nbecause alcohol or the drug
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.65,1:42:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of pushes the ego out of the way\Nthat's blocking it.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.65,1:42:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You sedate the ego.\NSo you get to feel the euphoria,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.72,1:42:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the euphoria is really the...\Nthe self with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.72,1:42:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're sensing now,\Nbecause the block to it has been sedated.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.81,1:42:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're addicted to,\Nyou're not addicted to the drug,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.32,1:43:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you're addicted to\Nthat wonderful state of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.57,1:43:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What you've experienced\Nthat you're never satisfied with any less.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.43,1:43:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So is it that those of us that become alcoholic,\Ndo we perceive that
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.43,1:43:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,state of drunkenness differently\Nthan those that don't?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.43,1:43:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I would think if everybody got that after a few drinks,\Nor is that a karmic thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.76,1:43:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is a drunk,\Nthey just haven't drunk enough yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.14,1:43:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You have another lifetime\Nor two out at sea,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.14,1:43:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and by golly,\Nwe used to hang out in the dives in the front,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.19,1:43:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and by golly, we had friendship,\Nand we hugged each other,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.19,1:43:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and we got boffed to the gills,\Nand we had fraternal love, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.19,1:43:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and camaraderie, we didn't feel lonely,\Nwe didn't feel fear,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.19,1:43:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we felt fantastic.\NNow why wouldn't anybody in their right mind
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.30,1:44:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,want to repeat that?\NI don't know, I never could figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.30,1:44:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So ultimately,\Ndoes that have to do with just the karma
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.46,1:44:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and where your soul is in its evolution\Nin that particular lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.46,1:44:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it has to do with a number of factors,\Nphysiologic and karmic,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.48,1:44:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and many of the people that,\Nif you ask with kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.48,1:44:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,how many lifetimes have they died of alcohol\Nbefore they finally got sober,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.48,1:44:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally the sixth time around they got it.\NSo you see a lot of people
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.57,1:44:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that have been in places like that,\Nin recovery groups,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.64,1:44:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and one of the fastest ways to God\Nis to hit bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.64,1:44:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to get to God fast,\Ngive a guy a couple cases of whiskey
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.00,1:44:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and leave him alone.\NI'll do anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.34,1:44:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do anything.\NHelp, I'll do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.36,1:44:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we used to tell him.\NHe said, what can I do to my husband?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.61,1:44:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, send him another case of whiskey\Nand he'll sit back and wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.19,1:45:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be happy to go to the recovery home.\NThe other question I had,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.84,1:45:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I may have misunderstood this,\Nbut I was under the impression that
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.84,1:45:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,people who have near-death experiences\Nhave a choice as to whether or not
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.84,1:45:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they want to come back.\NIs that true in that moment?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.84,1:45:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd if that's true,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.84,1:45:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,then was that their time of death\Nand the rest of the time after that
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.63,1:45:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is like bonus time?\NIt's punishment for not having left.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.23,1:45:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWell, things are not all that cut and dried.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.23,1:45:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, we want to differentiate\Nbetween near-death and out-of-body,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.68,1:45:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are completely different.\NI think everybody in our classes
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.01,1:45:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,are quite clear about that.\NOut-of-body, there isn't such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.01,1:45:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Near-death is transformative.\NAnd out-of-body, you calibrate the same
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.22,1:46:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,after as before,\Nwhich always seems surprising.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.26,1:46:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because now that you realize you're a spirit,\Nit seems to me your consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.26,1:46:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is a little bit of a jump, but it doesn't.\NNear-death is quite something different.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.61,1:46:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Near-death\Nis not exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.61,1:46:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's similar\Nto illumination,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.61,1:46:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's a near-death\Nkind of illumination.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.93,1:46:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an illumination that comes on spontaneously.\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.02,1:46:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be level 600.\NOne is more
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.69,1:46:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the witness to the phenomena\Nof whether or not this spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.69,1:46:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to re-enter this body or not.\NAlthough love,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.69,1:46:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,can be the determining factor.\NAnd several times,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.69,1:46:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially, it was love\Nthat decided
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.80,1:46:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to breathe it again,\Ntwo or three times, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.82,1:46:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was love for somebody\Nwho would view it as a big loss
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.82,1:47:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because they believe in death and all that.\NAnd they would think you died.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.14,1:47:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So for their sake, you breathe.\NSo the time of death that was determined
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.27,1:47:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,when the soul came into the body\Nis the time when that choice is made
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.27,1:47:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,as to whether or not they're going to come back?\NThis is too detailed
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.27,1:47:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a question. Whether in the near-death\Nexperience you are represented
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.27,1:47:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with an opportunity to reprogram\Nthe date of death
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.27,1:47:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,could be so, but I'd have to research\Nwhether that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.40,1:47:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost like you're given a chance\Nto shift the
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.10,1:47:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,time date or not.\NWell, when it comes on,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.10,1:47:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact it came on as I walked down the aisle here\None time, there was
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.10,1:47:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the permission to leave that was very strong.\NIt was like a powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.10,1:47:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,magnet pulling it to\Nexquisite realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.17,1:47:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that experience you have\Nthe knowingness of complete and total
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.17,1:47:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,permission. You have permission,\Nabsolute permission to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.17,1:48:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost an invitation to leave.\NAnd one doesn't know
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.52,1:48:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what is going to happen out of it.\NIf the body walked to the end and managed to
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.52,1:48:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,come back around the room, I guess that was the way\Nit was going to go. And if it fell down,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.52,1:48:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it was going to fall down.\NAnd I'd say, would I keep on walking or not?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.52,1:48:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, keep on walking, and if you're dying\Nthen the body falls down, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.52,1:48:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it didn't fall down,\Nso I presume that was not the time to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.52,1:48:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NNext time, I don't know though.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.02,1:48:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. A number of years ago\NI went to the front door of the home
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.02,1:48:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,where I lived, and I tried to take a\Nleft into my room.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.02,1:48:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And all at once, right here on the right side\Nof my head, I heard a yellow note
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.02,1:48:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in the kitchen. And I tried to ignore it,\Nand turn left into my room.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.02,1:48:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard what? A yellow note\Nin the kitchen. It was right
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.02,1:48:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,here, I could hear it. A yellow note?\NIn the kitchen. What's a yellow note?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.02,1:48:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's a yellow note?\NIt was just, I just heard the words
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.02,1:49:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,right here. I got into, I went through the front\Ndoor of my home, I tried to turn left
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.02,1:49:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,into my room. And all at\Nonce, I heard the words,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.02,1:49:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a yellow note in\Nthe kitchen. And I heard it
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.02,1:49:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,from right here. So, I kept\Nignoring it, and three to four times,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.02,1:49:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to turn left,\Nand it was almost as if I couldn't turn
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.02,1:49:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,left into my room, I kept hearing\Nthe same thing. So,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.02,1:49:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided, I stood there alone and out loud,\NI said, oh, alright, alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.02,1:49:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I decided to\Njust walk into the kitchen to see what was
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.02,1:49:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,going on. So, I did,\Nand I turned on the light, and on my
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.02,1:49:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,fruit bowl, there was a little yellow note\Nfrom my roommate, Jim.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.02,1:49:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It said, Crystal, your pineapple is ripe.\NThere was a yellow note
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.02,1:49:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in the kitchen. And then,\Nlast May, I awakened
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.02,1:49:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,one morning, and I wondered\Nwhat time it was. And I
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.02,1:49:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,heard, instead of on the right, I heard right\Nin the middle of my head,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.02,1:49:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard, it's ten o'clock, in a\Nvery clear voice. And I
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.02,1:50:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,thought to myself, oh no, it has to be eight or\Nnine. So, finally,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.02,1:50:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I put my head up, and I\Nlooked down across the room, and I looked
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.02,1:50:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,at the clock, it was ten o'clock.\NWhat's the question? The question
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.50,1:50:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is, where are these\Nthings coming from? Why was I no
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.50,1:50:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,notified that there was a yellow note in the kitchen?\NAnd why was I told it was ten o'clock
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.50,1:50:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when I couldn't visibly see it with my eyes?\NOh, well, that's just your spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.50,1:50:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's like out-of-body experience. Your\Nspirit can go all over the place and go back in the
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.50,1:50:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,body and report what's going on out there.\NOkay. Let me have one more question.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.50,1:50:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. I used to go into a box.\NYou know, you go to the Monroe Institute.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.59,1:50:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My spirit box. Anyway,\None of the things they teach you is how
Dialogue: 0,1:50:41.59,1:50:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to, you know, astral projection\Nand projection of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.59,1:50:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So I remember the training itself,\Nand the ten-hour toilet was set around.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.59,1:50:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And you were supposed to project\Nyour spirit into the box, read what's there,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.68,1:50:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and come back in, come back out again.\NSo you go into the box, and it said,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:57.77,1:51:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,hello. And I came back, and I said, hello.\NAnd I said, yep, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.77,1:51:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can train\Nyourself to do it at will.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.48,1:51:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My other question is, a number\Nof years ago, I was with a friend in
Dialogue: 0,1:51:10.48,1:51:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the living room in my apartment, and\Nalmost at the same time, we both
Dialogue: 0,1:51:14.48,1:51:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,perceived a screen of energy that was\Nright between us.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:18.48,1:51:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then a number of years after that,\NI was sitting in someone else's living room
Dialogue: 0,1:51:22.48,1:51:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,talking to this person, and all at\Nonce, it's as if, I guess, from the
Dialogue: 0,1:51:26.48,1:51:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,third eye, all at once I perceived\Na being up in the corner of the
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.48,1:51:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,room, and\Nthat same screen of energy, which I had
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.48,1:51:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,forgotten about, was going across the room\Nbehind the person I was talking to.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.48,1:51:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I've been told that you should\Nnot be in contact with these
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.48,1:51:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,beings, and I've been told that\Nyou should. So I don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.48,1:51:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if that's right, or even why it\Nhappened to me. I don't know anyone else
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.55,1:51:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who has perceived that.\NDo you think these are spirits?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.55,1:51:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I could see it. It was very different.\NIt was a different perception that opened up,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.55,1:52:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,as if you couldn't hear before, and then\Nall at once it was shocking, because it
Dialogue: 0,1:52:02.55,1:52:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,just opened up, and then you didn't have it.\NIt was like clairvoyance, you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.55,1:52:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It could have been. It was like an\Naltered state of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.55,1:52:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't through my eyes, but it was\Nthrough here. It was in the corner, and
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.55,1:52:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the image was about this big, and it was waving its arms.\NIt was pointing to astral domains,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.73,1:52:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and various\Nentities that you meet there.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.81,1:52:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You can learn to do it at will.\NMy explanation is
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.81,1:52:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,correct. You're pointing to various\Nastral domains, and you can
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.81,1:52:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,train yourself to do that.\NI'm telling you about the Menorah Institute. You can become
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.81,1:52:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,an expert at this, and travel all around\Nthe world, and
Dialogue: 0,1:52:38.81,1:52:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,join the circus.\NI knew I was going to get it for that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.81,1:52:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's because\NI'd say the aura can be trained
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.81,1:52:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave at will,\Nand also to investigate
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.81,1:52:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,other domains.\NWhen I was at Monroe,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.86,1:53:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked Bob Monroe. He had the most quiet,\Nbeautiful voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.86,1:53:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You felt like you were in the presence of Jesus\Nor something when he spoke. It was like a calmness.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.86,1:53:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't want you\Ngetting into too many games out in the astral
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.86,1:53:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,domains, so he\Ntrained you. You put on earphones,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.86,1:53:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and they\Nget picked up by the energy of the
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.86,1:53:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,cross speed. Let's say you got\Na frequency at a certain
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.86,1:53:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,level in this ear, and a frequency level\Nin this ear. He was an engineer,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.86,1:53:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a sound engineer.\NWhat you're picking up is
Dialogue: 0,1:53:30.86,1:53:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of the dissonance.\NYou can train yourself to go
Dialogue: 0,1:53:34.86,1:53:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,into consciousness state 10, 12,\N14, 15.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.86,1:53:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they went 10 to 15.\NYou go into an altered state of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.51,1:53:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In an altered state of consciousness,\Nyou can leave the
Dialogue: 0,1:53:47.51,1:53:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,body and explore various realms.\NHe had a whistle.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.80,1:53:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When you hear this whistle,\Nyou had to come back in the body and come home again.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.80,1:53:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,People get involved\Nin all kinds of adventures out in the astral
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.80,1:54:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,domains, all kinds of entities and\Nenergies. They've got weird programs.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.80,1:54:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all kinds of places.\NWith training, you can get two or three of you
Dialogue: 0,1:54:07.80,1:54:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can astral project together\Nand decide where you're going to meet, what domain
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.80,1:54:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and what dimension and what point.\NHe had this whistle. Of course, we got
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.80,1:54:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,earphones on. You're out of body\Nhaving various adventures and all of a sudden
Dialogue: 0,1:54:21.80,1:54:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you hear this beep, beep, beep.\NThat means you've got to come back in the body. Bang!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:25.80,1:54:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You go back in the body.\NI'm just telling you it can be
Dialogue: 0,1:54:30.53,1:54:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,trained.\NIt can be used
Dialogue: 0,1:54:34.53,1:54:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for certain things.\NOne of the things it can be used for is
Dialogue: 0,1:54:38.53,1:54:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,past life recall. You can actually\Nproject yourself into that dimension,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:42.53,1:54:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,relive the exact experience.\NIt can be useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:46.53,1:54:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people leave only\Nwhen they want and others will go out
Dialogue: 0,1:54:51.21,1:54:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously.\NSome people have a hard time staying in their body.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.52,1:54:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They have the will\Nto be there because they tend to drift off.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.52,1:55:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Sitting in the dentist's\Noffice, they go off.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:05.65,1:55:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other dimensions and other time frames\Nand the dentist is waiting for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.22,1:55:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very interesting.\NYou're discovering what's possible
Dialogue: 0,1:55:18.22,1:55:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,within the human psyche.\NThat's sort of an advancement
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.85,1:55:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because you start getting more evolved\Nas you start becoming aware of those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.30,1:55:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Astro projecting dreams.\NSpiritual experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.68,1:55:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,bring...\NThere's also a level
Dialogue: 0,1:55:39.68,1:55:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual evolution\Nwhich was quite interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.68,1:55:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to go through\Nin which the so-called paranormal
Dialogue: 0,1:55:47.68,1:55:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what classically call\Nthe cities, S-I-D-D-H-I-S
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.68,1:55:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly call them powers.\NIt's not actually powers
Dialogue: 0,1:55:56.01,1:56:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but you become clairvoyant.\NYou have a clairaudient.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.06,1:56:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something\Nwhere you hold something
Dialogue: 0,1:56:04.06,1:56:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know everything about who the person is\Nand I'll forget the term for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.35,1:56:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychometry.\NWhich came on spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.35,1:56:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and somebody left\Na scarf in my office
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.35,1:56:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and I picked up the scarf\Nand instantly it was like a loud knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.35,1:56:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of whose it was.\NI said, this is Estelle's.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:24.35,1:56:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, look what I found.\NShe said, give me my scarf.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:28.35,1:56:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So it came on spontaneously.\NBut there's a long period of time
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.35,1:56:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,where you have your clairaudient,\Nclairvoyant.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.39,1:56:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You have distant vision.\NYou can drive
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.57,1:56:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in a state you've never been before\Nwithout a map
Dialogue: 0,1:56:44.57,1:56:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and instantly know how to get past\Nall those lakes and all those complicated highways.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:48.57,1:56:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is picture where you're going\Nand you automatically go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:52.57,1:56:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's all kinds of different things.\NThe thing is not to get glamorized by them
Dialogue: 0,1:56:57.13,1:57:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or caught by them\Nand not to get fixated in them.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.13,1:57:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And not to have the ego\Nthink who it is because of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.13,1:57:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not you that's doing it.\NIt's the aura,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:09.13,1:57:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,this energy, the auric field\Nis doing that.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:13.13,1:57:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're the witness of it.\NSo you witness the very miraculous things
Dialogue: 0,1:57:17.13,1:57:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,happening all the time.\NAnd also it had the power to heal things.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:21.13,1:57:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,People would sit down next to you\Nand barely able
Dialogue: 0,1:57:25.13,1:57:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to stand it\Nand after five minutes they'd get up
Dialogue: 0,1:57:29.13,1:57:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and walk away perfectly fine.\NLeft their cane there, everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.18,1:57:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So that energy field is transformative.\NBut it's temporary,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:37.60,1:57:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at least in myself.\NIt was very strong for at least five years.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:41.60,1:57:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It could also affect\Nelectrical circuits
Dialogue: 0,1:57:46.50,1:57:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and electrical phenomena.\NElectronic equipment, essentially.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.50,1:57:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You could turn strobe lights on and off\Non various things.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:56.50,1:58:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Amplifiers, you know.\NA hundred watt amplifier,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:00.50,1:58:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a Macintosh amplifier went out.\NThe guy came to fix it
Dialogue: 0,1:58:04.50,1:58:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and as he walks toward it\NI saw the amplifier is perfect,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:08.50,1:58:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing wrong with it.\NIn my mind I'm thinking,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:12.50,1:58:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's perfect, there's nothing wrong with it.\NInstantly the hundred watt amplifier went on.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:16.50,1:58:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy says, holy smokes.\NHe said, how did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:20.78,1:58:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So I started talking to him about\Nthe Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:24.78,1:58:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I don't know, I was doing the Course in Miracles and all of a sudden this kind of stuff happened.\NSo I had exactly one copy left.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:28.78,1:58:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I had bought 50 of them\Nand given them away to everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:32.78,1:58:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I had exactly one copy left.\NSo this guy came to fix the amplifier,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:36.78,1:58:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessed what he thought was the miraculous,\Nsays I want the Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:40.78,1:58:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,got the one book, walked out, said thank you.\NAnd that's obviously the karmic reason
Dialogue: 0,1:58:44.78,1:58:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,why he came that day.
